fficient water for 30 minutes</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 3</span> Heat 3 cups of water in a deep non-stick pan. Add bay leaf, black cardamom, green cardamoms, cinnamon, cloves, salt, and the Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice. Now cover and cook till 3/4th done.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 4</span> Heat oil in another deep non-stick pan. Add caraway seeds and onion, and sauté.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 5</span> Add remaining ginger-garlic paste, coriander powder, and cumin powder. Mix well and sauté for a minute.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 6</span> Add marinated chicken pieces, mix well, cover, and cook for 2-3 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 7</span> Strain the Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice in a colander and set aside.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 8</span> Transfer half the chicken to another deep non-stick pan on heat. Spread half the strained Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice on top. Add ¼ cup of fried onions, mint leaves, and half the ginger strips. Drizzle ½ tbsp saffron milk, some ghee, and sprinkle some garam masala powder.</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n                </ul>','<ul>\r\n                  <li>750 GRAMS CHICKEN, CUT INTO 1 INCH PIECES ON BONE\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n                  <li>1½ CUPS DAAWAT BIRYANI BASMATI RICE\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n                  <li>½ CUP YOGURT\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n                  <li>SALT TO TASTE\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n                  <li>1½ TABLESPOONS GINGER-GARLIC PASTE\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n                  <li>1 TEASPOON GREEN CHILLI PASTE\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n  <li>1 TEASPOON RED CHILLI POWDER\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n  <li>1 BAY LEAF\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n  <li>1 BLACK CARDAMOM\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n  <li>5 GREEN CARDAMOMS\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n  <li>1 INCH CINNAMON\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>12-16 CLOVES\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n        \r\n<li>3 TABLESPOONS OIL\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n        \r\n<li>1 TEASPOON CARAWAY SEEDS (SHAHI JEERA)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n<li>1 MEDIUM ONION, SLICED\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n<li>1 TABLESPOON CORIANDER POWDER\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n<li>1 TABLESPOON CUMIN (JEERA) POWDER\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n<li>½ CUP FRIED ONIONS + FOR GARNISHING\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li>FEW FRESH MINT LEAVES\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li>1 INCH GINGER, CUT INTO STRIPS\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li>1 TABLESPOON SAFFRON MILK\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li>GHEE FOR DRIZZLING\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li>GARAM MASALA POWDER FOR SPRINKLING\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li>WHOLE WHEAT FLOUR (ATTA) DOUGH FOR SEALING\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li>FRESH MINT SPRIG FOR GARNISHING\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n        \r\n                </ul>','<ul>\r\n                   <li><span>STEP 1. </span>PUT CHICKEN PIECES IN A BOWL. ADD YOGURT, SALT, 1 TABLESPOON GINGER-GARLIC PASTE, GREEN CHILLI PASTE AND CHILLI POWDER, MIX WELL AND SET ASIDE TO MARINATE FOR 1 HOUR.\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n                  <li><span>STEP 2. </span>SOAK DAAWAT BIRYANI BASMATI RICE IN SUFFICIENT WATER FOR 30 MINUTES\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n                  <li><span>STEP 3. </span> HEAT 3 CUPS WATER IN A DEEP NON-STICK PAN. ADD BAY LEAF, BLACK CARDAMOM, GREEN CARDAMOMS, CINNAMON, CLOVES, SALT AND DRAINED DAAWAT BIRYANI BASMATI RICE, COVER AND COOK TILL 3/4TH DONE.\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n                  <li><span>STEP 4. </span>  HEAT OIL IN ANOTHER DEEP NON-STICK PAN. ADD CARAWAY SEEDS AND ONION AND SAUTÉ\r\n</li>\r\n<li><span>STEP 5. </span>ADD REMAINING GINGER-GARLIC PASTE, CORIANDER POWDER AND CUMIN POWDER, MIX WELL AND SAUTÉ FOR A MINUTE.\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li><span>STEP 6. </span>ADD MARINATED CHICKEN PIECES, MIX WELL, COVER AND COOK FOR 2-3 MINUTES.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li><span>STEP 7. </span> STRAIN THE DAAWAT BIRYANI BASMATI RICE IN A COLANDER AND SET ASIDE.\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li><span>STEP 8. </span>TRANSFER HALF THE CHICKEN TO ANOTHER DEEP NON-STICK PAN ON HEAT. SPREAD HALF THE STRAINED DAAWAT BIRYANI BASMATI RICE ON TOP. ADD ¼ CUP FRIED ONIONS, MINT LEAVES AND HALF THE GINGER STRIPS. DRIZZLE ½ TABLESPOON SAFFRON MILK, SOME GHEE AND SPRINKLE SOME GARAM MASALA POWDER.\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n                </ul>','daawat-biryani-rice','2021-12-28 17:02:04','2024-04-26 11:54:30'),(12,'Awadhi Chicken Biryani',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'<p>1</p>','<p>1</p>',NULL,'2','2','2','NonVeg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/30-awadhi-chicken-biryani-1655094139.png','media/recipes/thumbnail/30-awadhi-chicken-biryani-1655094139.png','2021-12-24','Transforming your Daawat Basmati Rice into lip-smacking Biryani is extremely simple, and this recipe will show you how!','Easy','40-45-minutes','5 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0Jf8gge7Do0&list=PLd4iYbCmUGHSF5VVs4eOPfVhKdVcSPCWn&index=13',1,'Awadhi Chicken Biryani Recipe | Authentic Flavor - Daawat','awadhi chicken biryani recipe','Experience the royal taste of Lucknow with Daawat\'s Awadhi Chicken Biryani Recipe. Perfectly spiced, this dish brings authentic Awadhi flavors to your kitchen.','awadhi-chicken-biryani',NULL,NULL,'7','winter-special','party,festival','lunch','<ul>\r\n<li>1½ cups <b>Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice</b></li>\r\n<li>750 grams chicken, cut into 1 inch pieces on the bone</li>\r\n<li>2 blade mace</li>\r\n<li>10 green cardamoms</li>\r\n<li>3 bay leaves</li>\r\n<li>Salt to taste</li>\r\n<li>4½ tbsps ghee + for drizzling</li>\r\n<li>1 inch cinnamon</li>\r\n<li>10 cloves</li>\r\n<li>1 medium onion, sliced</li>\r\n<li>½ tsp cumin seeds (jeera)</li>\r\n<li>3 green chillies</li>\r\n<li>½ cup yogurt</li>\r\n<li>1½ tbsps ginger-garlic paste</li>\r\n<li>½ tsp green cardamom powder</li>\r\n<li>½ tsp mace (javitri) powder</li>\r\n<li>A few saffron strands</li>\r\n<li>½ tsp rose water</li>\r\n<li>½ tsp screwpine essence (kewra)</li>\r\n<li>Whole wheat flour (atta) dough as required</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsps fried onions</li>\r\n<li>Few fresh mint leaves</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsps fresh cream</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp saffron milk</li>\r\n<li>Fresh mint sprig for garnishing</li>\r\n<li>Green cardamom powder for sprinkling</li>\r\n<li>1 inch ginger, cut into strips</li>\r\n<li>8-10 raisins</li>\r\n<li>8-10 cashew nuts, roasted</li>\r\n<li>Screwpine essence (kewra) for drizzling</li>\r\n<li>4 tsps saffron milk + for brushing</li>\r\n<li>Few fresh mint leaves</li>\r\n<li>Refined flour (maida) or whole wheat flour (atta) roti for covering</li>\r\n                </ul>','<ul>\r\n<li><span>Step 1</span> Soak the <b>Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice</b> in sufficient water for 30 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 2</span> Heat 3 cups of water in a deep non-stick pan. Add mace, 6 green cardamoms, 2 bay leaves, drained Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice, salt to taste. and 1½ tbsps ghee. Stir lightly, cover, and cook till 3/4th done.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 3</span> Heat 3 tbsps ghee in another deep non-stick pan. Add remaining green cardamoms, cinnamon, remaining bay leaves, cloves, onion, and cumin seeds. Now mix and sauté until onions are lightly browned.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 4</span> Put chicken pieces in a bowl.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 5</span> Slit green chillies and add to the bowl along with yogurt, ginger-garlic paste, salt, ¼ tsp cardamom powder, ¼ tsp mace powder, saffron, ¼ tsp rose water, and ¼ tsp screwpine essence. Mix well and set aside to marinate.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 6</span> Roll out wheat flour dough into a cylinder and place on a lid.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 7</span> Strain the Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice in a colander, and set it aside.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 8</span> Add the marinated chicken to the onions, spread the strained Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice on top, and then add fried onions and mint leaves. Drizzle cream, saffron milk, some ghee, the remaining rose water, remaining screwpine essence, remaining cardamom powder, and remaining mace powder. Place the lid with dough on top and press. Cook on low heat for 25-30 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 9</span> Garnish with mint sprig and serve hot.</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n                </ul>','<ul>\r\n                  <li>1½ CUPS DAAWAT BIRYANI BASMATI RICE\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n                  <li>750 GRAMS CHICKEN, CUT INTO 1 INCH PIECES ON BONE\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n                  <li>2 BLADE MACE\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n                  <li>10 GREEN CARDAMOMS\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n                  <li>3 BAY LEAVES\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n                  <li>SALT TO TASTE\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n  <li>4½ TABLESPOONS GHEE + FOR DRIZZLING\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n  <li>1 INCH CINNAMON\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n  <li>10 CLOVES\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n  <li>1 MEDIUM ONION, SLICED\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n  <li>½ TEASPOON CUMIN SEEDS (JEERA)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>3 GREEN CHILLIES\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n        \r\n<li>½ CUP YOGURT\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n        \r\n<li>1½ TABLESPOONS GINGER-GARLIC PASTE\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n<li>½ TEASPOON GREEN CARDAMOM POWDER\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n<li>½ TEASPOON MACE (JAVITRI) POWDER\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n<li>FEW SAFFRON STRANDS\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n<li>½ TEASPOON ROSE WATER\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li>½ TEASPOON SCREWPINE ESSENCE (KEWRA)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li>WHOLE WHEAT FLOUR (ATTA) DOUGH AS REQUIRED\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li>2 TABLESPOONS FRIED ONIONS\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li>FEW FRESH MINT LEAVES\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li>2 TABLESPOONS FRESH CREAM\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li>1 TABLESPOON SAFFRON MILK\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li>FRESH MINT SPRIG FOR GARNISHING\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li>GREEN CARDAMOM POWDER FOR SPRINKLING\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li>1 INCH GINGER, CUT INTO STRIPS\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li>8-10 RAISINS\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li>8-10 CASHEWNUTS, ROASTED\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li>SCREWPINE ESSENCE (KEWRA) FOR DRIZZLING\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li>4 TEASPOONS SAFFRON MILK + FOR BRUSHING\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li>FEW FRESH MINT LEAVES\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li>REFINED FLOUR (MAIDA) OR WHOLE WHEAT FLOUR (ATTA) ROTI FOR COVERING\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n        \r\n                </ul>','<ul>\r\n                   <li><span>STEP 1. </span>SOAK DAAWAT BIRYANI BASMATI RICE IN SUFFICIENT WATER FOR 30 MINUTES.\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n                  <li><span>STEP 2. </span>HEAT 3 CUPS WATER IN A DEEP NON-STICK PAN. ADD MACE, 6 GREEN CARDAMOMS, 2 BAY LEAVES, DRAINED DAAWAT BIRYANI BASMATI RICE, SALT AND 1½ TABLESPOONS GHEE. STIR LIGHTLY, COVER AND COOK TILL 3/4TH DONE.\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n                  <li><span>STEP 3. </span> HEAT 3 TABLESPOONS GHEE IN ANOTHER DEEP NON-STICK PAN. ADD REMAINING GREEN CARDAMOMS, CINNAMON, REMAINING BAY LEAF, CLOVES, ONION AND CUMIN SEEDS, MIX AND SAUTÉ TILL ONIONS ARE LIGHTLY BROWNED.\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n                  <li><span>STEP 4. </span> PUT CHICKEN PIECES IN A BOWL.\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li><span>STEP 5. </span> SLIT GREEN CHILLIES, ADD TO THE BOWL ALONGWITH YOGURT, GINGER-GARLIC PASTE, SALT, ¼ TEASPOON CARDAMOM POWDER, ¼ TEASPOON MACE POWDER, SAFFRON, ¼ TEASPOON ROSE WATER AND ¼ TEASPOON SCREWPINE ESSENCE AND MIX WELL. SET ASIDE TO MARINATE.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li><span>STEP 6. </span>ROLL OUT WHEAT FLOUR DOUGH INTO A CYLINDER AND PLACE ON A LID.\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li><span>STEP 7. </span> STRAIN THE DAAWAT BIRYANI BASMATI RICE IN A COLANDER. SET ASIDE.\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li><span>STEP 8. </span>ADD MARINATED CHICKEN TO THE ONIONS, SPREAD THE STRAINED DAAWAT BIRYANI BASMATI RICE ON TOP AND ADD FRIED ONIONS AND MINT LEAVES. DRIZZLE CREAM, SAFFRON MILK, SOME GHEE, REMAINING ROSE WATER, REMAINING SCREWPINE ESSENCE, REMAINING CARDAMOM POWDER AND REMAINING MACE POWDER, PLACE LID WITH DOUGH ON TOP AND PRESS. COOK ON LOW HEAT FOR 25-30 MINUTES.\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n<li><span>STEP 9. </span>GARNISH WITH MINT SPRIG AND SERVE HOT.\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n                </ul>','daawat-biryani-rice','2021-12-28 17:17:41','2024-04-26 12:34:54'),(13,'Prawn Biryani',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'<p>1</p>','<p>1</p>',NULL,'2','2','2','NonVeg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/28-prawn-biryani-1655093840.png','media/recipes/thumbnail/28-prawn-biryani-1655093840.png','2021-12-24','Transforming your Daawat Basmati Rice into lip-smacking Biryani is extremely simple, and this recipe will show you how!','Easy','40-45-minutes','5 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bFClEEqWS7M&list=PLd4iYbCmUGHSF5VVs4eOPfVhKdVcSPCWn&index=6&t=1s',1,'Prawn Biryani Recipe | Rich & Flavorful Seafood Delicacy - Daawat','prawn biryani recipe','Indulge in the aromatic and rich flavors of Daawat\'s Prawn Biryani Recipe. A perfect blend of spices and prawns makes this biryani a must-try seafood delicacy.','prawn-biryani',NULL,NULL,'indian','winter-special','party,festival','lunch','<ul>\r\n<li>600 gms prawn, shelled and deveined</li>\r\n<li>1½ cups <b>Daawat Dubar Basmati Rice</b></li>\r\n<li>Salt to taste</li>\r\n<li>1 star anise (phool chakri)</li>\r\n<li>6-8 cloves</li>\r\n<li>12-16 black peppercorns</li>\r\n<li>2 bay leaves</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsps lemon juice</li>\r\n<li>1 cup scraped fresh coconut</li>\r\n<li>3 green chillies</li>\r\n<li>12-16 fresh mint leaves + as required</li>\r\n<li>3 garlic cloves</li>\r\n<li>1 inch ginger, roughly chopped</li>\r\n<li>A few fresh coriander sprigs\r\n</li><li>½ cup fried onions + for garnishing</li>\r\n<li>3 tbsps ghee + for drizzling</li>\r\n<li>2 large onions, sliced</li>\r\n<li>1 inch ginger, cut into strips + for garnishing</li>\r\n<li>Garam masala powder for sprinkling</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp saffron milk</li>\r\n </ul>','<ul>\r\n<li><span>Step 1</span> Boil 3 cups water in a deep non-stick pan. Add <b>Daawat Dubar Basmati Rice</b>, salt, star anise, cloves, peppercorns, and bay leaves. Then cover and cook till rice is 3/4th done.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 2</span> Put prawns in a bowl. Add lemon juice and salt, and set aside.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 3</span> Blend together coconut, green chillies, mint leaves, garlic, chopped ginger, and coriander sprigs with water as required to a fine paste. Transfer to a bowl, add prawns and mix well. Add ¼ cup fried onions, mix, and set aside to marinate.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 4</span> Heat ghee in a deep non-stick pan. Add onions and sauté till translucent.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 5</span> Strain the Daawat Dubar Basmati Rice in a colander and spread half of it on the onions. Top up with half the marinated prawns and spread some of the strained Daawat Dubar Basmati Rice.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 6</span> Top with some fried onions and half the ginger strips, drizzle some ghee and sprinkle garam masala powder. Spread remaining marinated prawns and top with a layer of remaining strained Daawat Dubar Basmati Rice.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 7</span> Add remaining fried onions, sprinkle some garam masala powder, drizzle saffron milk and add some mint leaves. Cover and cook on low heat for 15-20 minutes. Remove from heat and let it rest for a few minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 8</span> Garnish with fried onions, mint leaves, and ginger strips, and serve hot.</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n                  <li>600 GRAMS PRAWNS, SHELLED AND DEVEINED\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n                  <li>1½ CUPS DAAWAT DUBAR BASMATI RICE\r\n</li>\r\n                  <li>SALT TO TASTE\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n                  <li>1 STAR ANISE (PHOOL CHAKRI)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n                  <li>6-8 CLOVES\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n                  <li>12-16 BLACK PEPPERCORNS\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n  <li>2 BAY LEAVES\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n  <li>2 TABLESPOONS LEMON JUICE\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n  <li>1 CUP SCRAPED FRESH COCONUT\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n  <li>3 GREEN CHILLIES\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n  <li>12-16 FRESH MINT LEAVES + AS REQUIRED\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<li>3 GARLIC CLOVES\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n        \r\n<li>1 INCH GINGER, ROUGHLY CHOPPED\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n        \r\n<li>FEW FRESH CORIANDER SPRIGS\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n<li>½ CUP FRIED ONIONS + FOR GARNISHING\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n<li>3 TABLESPOONS GHEE + FOR DRIZZLING\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n<li>2 LARGE ONIONS, SLICED\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n </li>\r\n<li>1 INCH GINGER, CUT INTO STRIPS + FOR GARNISHING\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li>GARAM MASALA POWDER FOR SPRINKLING\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li>1 TABLESPOON SAFFRON MILK\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n        \r\n                </ul>','<ul>\r\n                   <li><span>STEP 1. </span> BOIL 3 CUPS WATER IN A DEEP NON-STICK PAN. ADD DAAWAT DUBAR BASMATI RICE, SALT, STAR ANISE, CLOVES, PEPPERCORNS AND BAY LEAVES, COVER AND COOK TILL RICE IS 3/4TH DONE.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n                  <li><span>STEP 2. </span>PUT PRAWNS IN A BOWL. ADD LEMON JUICE AND SALT AND SET ASIDE.\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n                  <li><span>STEP 3. </span> BLEND TOGETHER COCONUT, GREEN CHILLIES, MINT LEAVES, GARLIC, CHOPPED GINGER AND CORIANDER SPRIGS WITH WATER AS REQUIRED TO A FINE PASTE. TRANSFER TO A BOWL, ADD PRAWNS AND MIX WELL. ADD ¼ CUP FRIED ONIONS, MIX AND SET ASIDE TO MARINATE.\r\n</li>\r\n                  <li><span>STEP 4. </span> HEAT GHEE IN A DEEP NON-STICK PAN. ADD ONIONS AND SAUTÉ TILL TRANSLUCENT.\r\n</li>\r\n<li><span>STEP 5. </span>STRAIN THE DAAWAT DUBAR BASMATI RICE IN A COLANDER AND SPREAD HALF OF IT ON THE ONIONS. TOP WITH HALF THE MARINATED PRAWNS AND SPREAD SOME OF THE STRAINED DAAWAT DUBAR BASMATI RICE.\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li><span>STEP 6. </span>TOP WITH SOME FRIED ONIONS AND HALF THE GINGER STRIPS, DRIZZLE SOME GHEE AND SPRINKLE GARAM MASALA POWDER. SPREAD REMAINING MARINATED PRAWNS AND TOP WITH A LAYER OF REMAINING STRAINED DAAWAT DUBAR BASMATI RICE.\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li><span>STEP 7. </span> ADD REMAINING FRIED ONIONS, SPRINKLE SOME GARAM MASALA POWDER, DRIZZLE SAFFRON MILK AND ADD SOME MINT LEAVES. COVER AND COOK ON LOW HEAT FOR 15-20 MINUTES. REMOVE FROM HEAT AND LET IT REST FOR A FEW MINUTES.\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n<li><span>STEP 8. </span>GARNISH WITH FRIED ONIONS, MINT LEAVES, GINGER STRIPS AND SERVE HOT.\r\n\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n\r\n                </ul>','daawat-biryani-rice','2021-12-28 17:24:09','2024-04-26 12:28:57'),(15,'Restaurant Style Veg Biryani',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'<p>1</p>','<p>1</p>',NULL,'2','2','2','Veg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/27-restuarant-style-veg-biryani-1655093769.png','media/recipes/thumbnail/27-restuarant-style-veg-biryani-1655093769.png','2021-12-24','Transforming your Daawat Basmati Rice into lip-smacking Biryani is extremely simple, and this recipe will show you how!','Easy','30-min','5 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BDusjCR5nvQ&list=PLd4iYbCmUGHSF5VVs4eOPfVhKdVcSPCWn&index=11',1,'Restaurant-Style Veg Biryani Recipe | Aromatic & Savory - Daawat','restaurant style veg biryani recipe','Experience the joy of cooking with Daawat\'s Restaurant-Style Veg Biryani Recipe. Packed with the vibrant flavors of fresh vegetables and aromatic spices, this biryani mimics the authentic taste of your favorite restaurants. Perfect for any occasion.','restaurant-style-veg-biryani',NULL,NULL,'indian','always-loved','party,everyday-meal,festival','party','<ul>\r\n<li>1½ cups <b>Daawat Super Basmati Rice</b>, soaked for 30 minutes and drained</li>\r\n<li>2 medium carrots, peeled, and cut into diamonds</li>\r\n<li>10-12 cauliflower florets</li>\r\n<li>5-6 French beans, cut into pieces</li>\r\n<li>4-5 baby corns, cut into diamonds</li>\r\n<li>¼ cup green peas</li>\r\n<li>100 grams cottage cheese (paneer), cut into small cubes</li>\r\n<li>4 tbsps ghee + for drizzling and brushing</li>\r\n<li>1 inch cinnamon</li>\r\n<li>5 green cardamoms</li>\r\n<li>1 blade mace (javitri)</li>\r\n<li>10-12 cloves</li>\r\n<li>10-12 black peppercorns</li>\r\n<li>1 bay leaf</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp caraway seeds (shahi jeera)</li>\r\n<li>1 large onion, sliced</li>\r\n<li>2 green chillies</li>\r\n<li>1½ tbsps ginger-garlic paste</li>\r\n<li>¼ tsp turmeric powder</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp coriander-cumin powder</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp red chilli powder</li>\r\n<li>½ cup fresh tomato puree</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsps fresh cream</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp chopped fresh coriander leaves</li>\r\n<li>4 tbsps fried onions</li>\r\n<li>Green cardamom powder for sprinkling</li>\r\n<li>1 inch ginger, cut into strips</li>\r\n<li>8-10 raisins</li>\r\n<li>8-10 cashew nuts, roasted</li>\r\n<li>Screwpine essence (kewra) for drizzling</li>\r\n<li>4 tsps saffron milk + for brushing</li>\r\n<li>A few fresh mint leaves</li>\r\n<li>Refined flour (maida) or whole wheat flour (atta) roti for covering</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n <li><span>Step 1</span> Heat ghee in a deep non-stick deep pan. Add cinnamon, green cardamoms, mace, cloves, peppercorns, and bay leaf, and then sauté till fragrant.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 2</span> Heat remaining ghee in another deep non-stick pan. Add caraway seeds and sauté for a minute.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 3</span> Add Daawat Super Basmati Rice to the sautéed spices and mix well. Add 3 cups of hot water too.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 4</span> Add onions to caraway seeds, mix, and sauté till onions turn translucent.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 5</span> Add salt to the rice, cover, and cook till 3/4th done. Strain and set aside.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 6</span> Break green chillies, add to the onions, mix, and sauté for a minute. Add ginger-garlic paste, mix well, and sauté.\r\n</li><li><span>Step 7</span> Add turmeric powder, coriander-cumin powder, ,and chilli powder, and mix well. Add tomato puree, mix well, and cook for 1-2 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 8</span> Add carrots, cauliflower, French beans, and baby corn and mix. Add salt and cream, and mix well again. Add coriander leaves, green peas, and cottage cheese cubes. Mix lightly and cook for 3-4 minutes</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 9</span> Preheat oven to 180º C.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 10</span> Spread a layer of cooked vegetables in a handi and top up with a layer of strained Daawat Super Basmati Rice. Sprinkle 2 tbsps fried onions, cardamom powder, half the ginger strips, raisins and cashew nuts. Drizzle some screwpine essence, 2 tsps saffron milk, and some ghee, and sprinkle some mint leaves.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 11</span> Top up with a layer of the remaining cooked vegetables and the remaining strained Daawat Super Basmati Rice. Sprinkle some cardamom powder, the remaining fried onions, the remaining ginger strips, and some mint leaves. Drizzle some screwpine essence and the remaining saffron milk.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 12</span> Cover the handi with roti, brush the top with some ghee and saffron milk. Place the handi in the preheated oven and cook till the top turns reddish.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 13</span> Serve hot.</li>\r\n</ul>','<p><br></p>','<div><br></div><ul>\r\n                </ul>','daawat-biryani-rice','2021-12-28 17:32:41','2024-04-26 12:00:47'),(16,'Brown Rice Cakes',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'<p>1</p>','<p>1</p>',NULL,'1','1','1','Veg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/01-brown-rice-cakes-1654853161.png','media/recipes/thumbnail/brown-rice-cakes-1648796599.png','2021-12-24','Transforming your Daawat Basmati rice into a lip-smacking Biryani is extremely simple and this recipe will show you how!','Easy','30-min','3 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=f766tz8FawQ&list=PLd4iYbCmUGHSNjsb9hxRvNp3UsJDHMvui&index=14&t=1s',1,'Brown Rice Cakes Recipe | Healthy & Crispy Snack - Daawat','brown rice cakes recipe','Discover Daawat\'s Brown Rice Cakes Recipe for a healthy, crispy snack you can enjoy anytime. Made with nutritious brown rice, these cakes are perfect for guilt-free munching.','brown-rice-cakes',NULL,NULL,'fusion','always-loved','party','party,healthy,lunch','<ul>\r\n<li>1½ cups <b>Daawat Quick Cooking Brown Basmati Rice</b></li>\r\n<li>Salt to taste</li>\r\n<li>2 fresh red chillies, chopped</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsps chopped fresh coriander</li>\r\n<li>Crushed black peppercorns to taste</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsps toasted white sesame seeds</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp ginger-garlic paste</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsps corn flour</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp red chilli powder</li>\r\n<li>½ tsp turmeric powder</li>\r\n<li>¼ tsp garam masala powder</li>\r\n<li>½ tsp dried mango powder (amchur)</li>\r\n<li>Oil for shallow frying</li>\r\n<li>Tomato ketchup to serve</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n <li><span>Step 1</span> Take <b>Daawat Quick Cooking Brown Basmati Rice</b> in a bowl. Add sufficient water and wash for 2-3 times.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 2</span> Again add sufficient water, and this time let it soak for 25-30 minutes. Drain the water.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 3</span> Boil 5-6 cups water in a deep non-stick pan. Add salt, soaked rice, and mix well. Cook for 15 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 4</span> Drain the water and set the rice aside.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 5</span> Transfer the cooked rice in a bowl. Add red chillies, coriander leaves, crushed black peppercorns, white sesame seeds, ginger- garlic paste, corn flour, red chilli powder, turmeric powder, garam masala powder, dried mango powder, and salt, and mix well.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 6</span> Mash well with hands. Divide the mixture into equal portions and shape into tikkis. These are the cakes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 7</span> Heat sufficient oil in a shallow non-stick pan. Arrange the prepared cakes and shallow fry on medium heat for 2 minutes or till the underside is golden brown and crisp.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 8</span> Flip and cook the other side for 2 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 9</span> Drain on absorbent paper and serve hot with tomato ketchup.</li>\r\n</ul>','<p><br></p>','<div><br></div><ul>\r\n                </ul>','daawat-brown-rice','2021-12-30 12:28:26','2024-04-26 12:30:21'),(19,'Brown Rice & Red Beans Salad',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'<p>1</p>','<p>1</p>',NULL,'1','1','1','Veg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/brown-rice-&-red-beans-salad-1640861856.jpg','media/recipes/thumbnail/brown-rice-&-red-beans-salad-thumb-1640861856.jpg','2021-12-24','Transforming your Daawat Basmati rice into lip-smacking Biryani is extremely simple, and this recipe will show you how!','Easy','50-55-minutes','5 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-zDMu3p5Uwo&list=PLd4iYbCmUGHSNjsb9hxRvNp3UsJDHMvui&index=13&t=2s',1,'Brown Rice Red Beans Salad Recipe | Nutritious & Delicious - Daawat','brown rice red beans salad recipe','Indulge in Daawat\'s Brown Rice Red Beans Salad, a perfect blend of health & taste. This recipe packs fiber, protein & flavor for a wholesome meal or side dish.','brown-rice-red-beans-salad',NULL,NULL,'fusion','always-loved','party,everyday-meal','party,healthy,lunch','<ul>\r\n<li>1 cup boiled red kidney beans</li>\r\n<li>1½ cups <b>Daawat Quick Cooking Brown Basmati Rice</b></li>\r\n<li>Salt to taste</li>\r\n<li>2 tsps mustard paste</li>\r\n<li>1½ tsps dried mixed herbs</li>\r\n<li>Crushed black peppercorns to taste</li>\r\n<li>1½ tbsps lemon juice</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsps extra virgin olive oil</li>\r\n<li>1 large avocado</li>\r\n<li>½ medium red capsicum, seeded, and cut into triangles</li>\r\n<li>½ medium yellow capsicum, seeded, and cut into triangles</li>\r\n<li>½ medium green capsicum, seeded, and cut into triangles</li>\r\n<li>1 large carrot, peeled, cut into triangles, and blanched</li>\r\n<li>6-8 assorted cherry tomatoes, halved</li>\r\n<li>½ cup boiled corn kernels</li>\r\n<li>6-8 toasted walnuts, broken</li>\r\n<li>2-3 tbsps assorted micro greens</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li><span>Step 1</span> Take <b>Daawat Quick Cooking Brown Basmati Rice</b> in a bowl. Add sufficient water and wash for 2-3 times.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 2</span> Now once again add sufficient water and let it soak for 25-30 minutes. Drain the water.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 3</span> Boil 5-6 cups of water in a deep non-stick pan. Add salt, soaked rice, and mix well. Cook for 15 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 4</span> Drain the water and set the rice aside to cool down.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 5</span> For the dressing, take mustard paste in a bowl. Add dried mixed herbs, salt, crushed black peppercorns, lemon juice, and mix well. Add extra virgin olive oil and again mix well.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 6</span> Cut the avocado into 2 parts and remove the seeds. Further cut it into small pieces and transfer in a bowl.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 7</span> Add red capsicum, yellow capsicum, green capsicum, carrots, cherry tomatoes, corn kernels, toasted walnuts, red kidney beans, and cooked rice, and mix well.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 8</span> Pour the prepared dressing over, add micro greens and mix.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 9</span> Transfer into a serving plate and serve.</li>\r\n</ul>','<div><br></div>','<div><br></div>','daawat-brown-rice','2021-12-30 15:27:35','2024-04-26 12:31:04'),(20,'Brown Rice Pulao',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'<p>1</p>','<p>1</p>',NULL,'2','2','2','Veg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/34-brown-rice-pulao-1654856657.png','media/recipes/thumbnail/34-brown-rice-pulao-1654856657.png','2021-12-24','Transforming your Daawat Basmati Rice into lip-smacking Pulav is extremely simple, and this recipe will show you how!','Easy','30-min','5 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DknLhIIlABE&list=PLd4iYbCmUGHSNjsb9hxRvNp3UsJDHMvui&index=3&t=20s',1,'Healthy Brown Rice Pulao Recipe | Nutritious & Delicious - Daawat','brown rice pulao','Savor the goodness of whole grains with Daawat\'s Brown Rice Pulao Recipe. This nutritious dish combines the rich flavors of veggies and spices with the health benefits of brown rice. Perfect for a hearty meal, enjoy a delicious twist on traditional pulao. Try it today.','brown-rice-pulao',NULL,NULL,'fusion,indian','always-loved','everyday-meal','dinner,healthy,lunch','<ul>\r\n<li>1½ cups <b>Daawat Quick Cooking Brown Basmati Rice</b></li>\r\n<li>2 tbsps ghee</li>\r\n<li>1 inch cinnamon stick</li>\r\n<li>1 bay leaf</li>\r\n<li>8-10 black peppercorns</li>\r\n<li>5-6 cloves</li>\r\n<li>2-3 green cardamoms</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp cumin seeds</li>\r\n<li>2-3 green chillies, slit</li>\r\n<li>1 medium carrot, peeled cut into ½ inch diamonds</li>\r\n<li>8-10 small cauliflower florets</li>\r\n<li>4-5 French beans, stringed and diagonally cut into ½ inch pieces</li>\r\n<li>3-4 button mushrooms, quartered</li>\r\n<li>A pinch of red chilli powder</li>\r\n<li>A large pinch of turmeric powder</li>\r\n<li>Salt to taste</li>\r\n<li>¼ cup shelled green peas</li>\r\n<li>1½ tbsps chopped fresh coriander</li>\r\n<li>Coriander sprig for garnish</li>\r\n<li>Boondi raita to serve</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li><span>Step 1</span> Take <b>Daawat Quick Cooking Brown Basmati Rice</b> in a bowl. Add sufficient water and wash for 2-3 times.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 2</span> Add sufficient water and soak for 25-30 minutes. Drain the water.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 3</span> Heat ghee in a non-stick pan. Add cinnamon stick, bay leaf, black peppercorns, cloves, green cardamoms, and cumin seeds, and sauté until fragrant.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 4</span> Add green chillies and sauté for 1 minute. Add carrot, cauliflower, French beans, and button mushrooms, and again sauté for 1-2 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 5</span> Add red chilli powder, turmeric powder, and salt, and mix well. Cook for 1-2 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 6</span> Add green peas and soaked brown rice and mix with a light hand. Add 2½ cups of hot water and again mix well.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 7</span> Add coriander leaves, mix lightly, cover, and cook on high heat for 15 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 8</span> Transfer on a serving plate, garnish with coriander sprig, and now serve hot with boondi raita.</li>\r\n</ul>',NULL,NULL,'daawat-brown-rice','2021-12-30 15:57:41','2024-04-26 11:58:23'),(21,'Quick Chicken Pulao',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'<p>1</p>','<p>1</p>',NULL,'2','2','2','NonVeg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/quick-chiken-pulav-1640865337.jpg','media/recipes/thumbnail/quick-chiken-pulav-thumb-1640865337.jpg','2021-12-24','Transforming your Daawat Basmati Rice into lip-smacking Pulav is extremely simple, and this recipe will show you how!','Easy','50-55-minutes','5 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VyHh_3s9vaA&list=PLd4iYbCmUGHTjukrnZ9d-PYJYPzxHAwGl&index=3',1,'Quick Chicken Pulao Recipe for a Delicious Meal - Daawat','quick chicken pulao recipe','Craving a delicious meal? Try our Quick Chicken Pulao Recipe, an easy and flavorful way to enjoy chicken and rice. Perfect for any day, get cooking with Daawat now!','quick-chicken-pulao',NULL,NULL,'indian','always-loved','party,everyday-meal','dinner,lunch','<ul>\r\n  <li> 1 1/2 cup <b>Daawat pulav basmati rice</b></li>\r\n  <li> 2 1/2 tsp ghee</li>\r\n  <li> 400 gm chicken </li>\r\n  <li> 1/2 inch cinnamon stick</li>\r\n  <li> 3-4 green cardamoms</li>\r\n  <li> 7-8 black peppercorns</li>\r\n  <li> 5-6 cloves</li>\r\n  <li> 2-3 green chillies</li>\r\n  <li> 1-inch ginger cut into thin strips </li>\r\n  <li> 1 cut onion</li>\r\n  <li> 1 cup fresh tomato puree</li>\r\n  <li> 1/4 cup yoghurt</li>\r\n  <li> 3 tbsp coriander leaves</li>\r\n  <li> 2 cups chicken stock</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <p><b>Masala</b></p>\r\n  <li>Salt as per taste</li>\r\n<li>1 1/2 tsp red chilli powder</li>\r\n<li>1/4 tsp turmeric powder</li>\r\n<li>1 1/2 tsp coriander powder</li>\r\n<li>2 tsp garam masala</li>\r\n<li>Raita to serve</li>\r\n<li>Coriander spring for garnish</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li><span>Step 1</span> Take the required Daawat Pulav Basmati Rice in a bowl. Add sufficient water and clean the rice properly 2-3 times.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 2</span> Once cleaned, soak the rice in fresh water for about 20 minutes. Once it\'s done, drain the excess water and set it aside.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 3</span> In a non-stick pan on low flame add some ghee. Once melted, add the chicken to the pan and sauté it for 2-3 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 4</span> Now, to prepare the masala for the pulav, in a pan add 2-3 tsp melted ghee, cinnamon stick, cardamom, black pepper, cloves, green chilli, ginger, and onion. Now sauté till it turns translucent and golden brown in colour.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 5</span> Now, pour fresh tomato puree into the masala. Along with it, add salt as per taste. Stir it continuously for 2-3 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 6</span> Add red chilli powder, turmeric powder, coriander powder, and garam masala. Cook the ingredients well until the oil separates.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 7</span> Lower the flame, and add yoghurt to the pan. Mix all the ingredients properly.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 8</span> Once the masala is ready, add some coriander leaves and the chicken. Sauté it for 1-2 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 9</span> Finally, add the cooked rice and chicken stock, and evenly spread the rice in the pan. Now, gently mix all the ingredients until well combined.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 9</span> Cover the pan with a lid and cook on low flame for 20-25 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 9</span> Garnish the dish with coriander spring. Now, serve and Enjoy the meal with raita!</li>\r\n</ul>',NULL,'<div><br></div>','daawat-pulav-rice','2021-12-30 16:00:16','2024-04-26 12:47:43'),(22,'Soya Keema Matar Pulao',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'<p>1</p>','<p>1</p>',NULL,'2','2','2','Veg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/soya-keema-matar-pulao-1640867625.jpg','media/recipes/thumbnail/soya-keema-matar-pulao-thumb-1640867625.jpg','2021-12-24','Transforming your Daawat Basmati Rice into lip-smacking Pulav is extremely simple, and this recipe will show you how!','Easy','50-55-minutes','5 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PDFIUZ5GqQc&list=PLd4iYbCmUGHTjukrnZ9d-PYJYPzxHAwGl&index=10',1,'Soya Keema Matar Pulao Recipe | Vegetarian Delight - Daawat','soya keema matar pulao recipe','Master the art of making Soya Keema Matar Pulao with Daawat\'s easy recipe. A savory vegetarian feast that promises richness in every bite. Perfect meal choice.','soya-keema-matar-pulao',NULL,NULL,'indian','winter-special','everyday-meal','dinner,lunch','<ul>\r\n  <li>1 1/2 cups Daawat Pulav Basmati Rice</li>\r\n<li>3 tbsp ghee</li>\r\n<li>5-6 black pepper</li>\r\n<li>3-4 green cardamom</li>\r\n<li>3-4 cloves</li>\r\n<li>1-inch cinnamon stick</li>\r\n<li>1 bay leaf</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp cumin seeds</li>\r\n<li>1 1/2 tbsp garlic</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp ginger</li>\r\n<li>2-3 green chillies</li>\r\n<li>2 onions</li>\r\n<li>1 1/4 cups soya granules</li>\r\n<li>1/4 cup green peas</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsp coriander leaves</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp lemon juice</li>\r\n<li>2 1/2 cup hot water</li>\r\n<li>Garnish with coriander leaves</li>\r\n<li>Raita to serve</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Masala</b></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>1/2 tsp red chilli powder</li>\r\n<li>3/4 tsp turmeric powder</li>\r\n<li>3/4 tsp cumin powder</li>\r\n<li>1/2 tsp coriander powder</li>\r\n<li>1/2 tsp garam masala</li>\r\n<li>Salt as per taste</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li><span>Step 1</span> Take a bowl and add Daawat Pulav Basmati Rice into it. First, wash it rigorously with water 2-3 times.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 2</span> Take fresh water in the bowl and soak the Basmati Rice for 20-25 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 3</span> Wash the onions and finely chop them along with the green chilli. Also, shell the green peas beforehand. Keep them aside for later use.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 4</span> To start cooking, take a non-stick pan on low flame and add melted ghee into it.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 5</span> Add black pepper, green cardamom, cloves, cinnamon sticks, bay leaf, and cumin seeds. Sauté the masala for a few minutes till they are mixed properly and aromatic.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 6</span> Now, add lesson paste, garlic paste, chopped green chillies, and cut onion into the pan. Sauté for 2-3 minutes until the colour changes to medium brown.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 7</span> While cooking on medium flame, add fine soya granules on top. Spread it properly and sauté it until combined for about a minute.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 8</span> Finally for the masala, add red chilli powder, turmeric powder, cumin powder, coriander powder, garam masala, and salt as per taste. All the spices must be mixed well.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 9</span> Lastly, add green peas and cooked rice into the pan. Spread the Basmati Rice evenly in the pan.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 10</span> Top the dish with some coriander leaves, and add lemon juice to the ingredients for a better flavor. Mix all ingredients gently.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 11</span> Heat 2 ½ cups of hot water and add to the dish. Mix it well on high flame for a few minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 12</span> Now, with an aluminum lid, cover the pan for 20-25 minutes and let the dish cook.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 13</span> Once ready, fluff the rice gently and serve the dish hot with raita to add to the taste.</li>\r\n</ul>','<div><br></div>','<div><br></div>','daawat-pulav-rice','2021-12-30 17:02:15','2024-04-26 12:27:30'),(23,'Paneer Makhana Pulao',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'<p>1</p>','<p>1</p>',NULL,'2','2','2','Veg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/paneer-makhana-pulao-1640869663.jpg','media/recipes/thumbnail/paneer-makhana-pulao-thumb-1640869663.jpg','2021-12-24','Transforming your Daawat Basmati rice into a lip-smacking Biryani is extremely simple and this recipe will show you how!','Easy','50-55-minutes','5 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YGlHX-iBPQA&list=PLd4iYbCmUGHTjukrnZ9d-PYJYPzxHAwGl&index=12',1,'Paneer Makhana Pulao Recipe | Easy & Delicious Pulao - Daawat','paneer makhana pulao recipe','Dive into the flavors of Paneer Makhana Pulao with our simple recipe. A delicious, nutritious meal ideal for family gatherings or special moments. Step by step guide available.','paneer-makhana-pulao',NULL,NULL,'indian','always-loved','party,everyday-meal','healthy','<ul>\r\n <li>1 1/2 cups of <b>Daawat Pulav Basmati Rice</b></li>\r\n<li>3 tbsps of oil</li>\r\n<li>5-6 dried urad dal nuggets</li>\r\n<li>3-4 green cardamoms</li>\r\n<li>5-6 black peppercorns</li>\r\n<li>1/2 tbsp of ginger\r\n</li><li>1/2 tbsp of asafoetida (hing)</li>\r\n<li>2 sliced onions</li>\r\n<li>1 cut tomato</li>\r\n<li>3 chopped potatoes</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsps of coriander leaves</li>\r\n<li>2 cups of hot water</li>\r\n<li>Coriander leaves for garnishing</li>\r\n<li>Serve with burani raita</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Masala</b></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Salt as per taste</li>\r\n<li>1/2 tbsp of red chilli powder</li>\r\n<li>1/2 tbsp of turmeric powder</li>\r\n<li>1/2 tbsp of coriander powder</li>\r\n<li>1/2 tbsp of cumin powder</li>\r\n<li>3/4 tbsp of garam masala powder</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li>Step 1 In a bowl, add Daawat Pulav Basmati Rice. Take some water and clean it properly 2-3 times.</li>\r\n<li>Step 2 Once cleaned, add fresh water to the bowl and let it soak for 20-25 minutes.</li>\r\n<li>Step 3 To start the recipe, take a deep pan and add oil on a low flame. Now, add dried urad dal nuggets and fry till the color turns golden brown. Once done, take a plate and take them out to cool down.</li>\r\n<li>Step 4 Now add green cardamom, black peppercorns, ginger, asafoetida, some finely chopped onion, and tomato. Stir the vegetables for 2-3 minutes on medium flame.</li>\r\n<li>Step 5 Now for the masala, add salt as per taste, red chili powder, turmeric powder, coriander powder, cumin powder, and garam masala powder. Stir all the spices for about a minute until aromatic.</li>\r\n<li>Step 6 In the same pan, add cut potatoes and mix them well.</li>\r\n<li>Step 7 Finally, add the fried urad dal nuggets and the coriander leaves into the pan.</li>\r\n<li>Step 8 Evenly add the cooked rice and mix well until all the ingredients are combined.</li>\r\n</ul>','<div><br></div>','<div><br></div>','daawat-pulav-rice','2021-12-30 17:32:34','2024-04-26 12:34:13'),(24,'Aloo Wadi Pulao',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'<p>1</p>','<p>1</p>',NULL,'2','2','2','Veg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/aloo-wadi-pulao-1640871903.jpg','media/recipes/thumbnail/aloo-wadi-pulao-thumb-1640871903.jpg','2021-12-24','Transforming your Daawat Basmati rice into lip-smacking Pulav is extremely simple, and this recipe will show you how!','Easy','50-55-minutes','5 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=17XmZWvMUIs&list=PLd4iYbCmUGHTjukrnZ9d-PYJYPzxHAwGl&index=16',1,'Aloo Wadi Pulao Recipe | Unique & Tasty - Daawat','aloo wadi pulao recipe','Try the unique Aloo Wadi Pulao Recipe from Daawat. A flavorsome combination of potatoes, dried lentil dumplings, and rice, perfect for a comforting meal.','aloo-wadi-pulao',NULL,NULL,'indian','summer-specials','everyday-meal','dinner,lunch','<ul>\r\n<li>1 1/2 cups of Daawat Pulav Basmati Rice</li>\r\n<li>3 tbsps of oil</li>\r\n<li>5-6 dried urad dal nuggets</li>\r\n<li>3-4 green cardamoms</li>\r\n<li>5-6 black peppercorns</li>\r\n<li>1/2 tbsp of ginger</li>\r\n<li>1/2 tbsp of asafoetida (hing</li>\r\n<li>2 sliced onions</li>\r\n<li>1 cut tomato</li>\r\n<li>3 chopped potatoes</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsps of coriander leaves</li>\r\n<li>2 cups of hot water</li>\r\n<li>Coriander leaves for garnishing</li>\r\n<li>Serve with burani raita</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><b>Masala</b></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Salt as per taste</li>\r\n<li>1/2 tbsp of red chilli powder</li>\r\n<li>1/2 tbsp of turmeric powder</li>\r\n<li>1/2 tbsp of coriander powder</li>\r\n<li>1/2 tbsp of cumin powder</li>\r\n<li>3/4 tbsp of garam masala powder</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n  <li><span>Step 1</span> In a bowl, add Daawat Pulav Basmati Rice. Take some water and clean it properly 2-3 times.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 2</span> Once cleaned, add fresh water to the bowl and let it soak for 20-25 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 3</span> To start the recipe, take a deep pan and add oil on a low flame. Now, add dried urad dal nuggets and fry till the color turns golden brown. Once done, take a plate and take them out to cool down.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 4</span> Now add green cardamom, black peppercorns, ginger, asafoetida, some finely chopped onion, and tomato. Stir the vegetables for 2-3 minutes on medium flame.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 5</span> Now for the masala, add salt as per taste, red chili powder, turmeric powder, coriander powder, cumin powder, and garam masala powder. Stir all the spices for about a minute until aromatic.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 6</span> In the same pan, add cut potatoes and mix them well.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 7</span> Finally, add the fried urad dal nuggets and the coriander leaves into the pan.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 8</span> Evenly add the cooked rice and mix well until all the ingredients are combined.</li>\r\n</ul>','<div><br></div>','<div><br></div>','daawat-pulav-rice','2021-12-30 18:13:13','2024-04-26 12:29:39'),(25,'Kerala Style Mutton Biryani',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'<p>1</p>','<p>1</p>',NULL,'2','2','2','NonVeg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/26-kerala-style-mutton-biryani-1655093694.png','media/recipes/thumbnail/26-kerala-style-mutton-biryani-1655093694.png','2021-12-24','Transforming your Daawat Basmati Rice into lip-smacking Kerala Style Mutton Biryani is extremely simple, and this recipe will show you how!','Easy','50-55-minutes','5 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gIe1B9nFBos&list=PLd4iYbCmUGHSF5VVs4eOPfVhKdVcSPCWn&index=9',1,'Authentic Kerala Style Mutton Biryani Recipe - Daawat','kerala style mutton biryani recipe','Experience the richness of South Indian cuisine with this Kerala Style Mutton Biryani Recipe from Daawat. Aromatic spices, tender mutton, and fragrant rice come together to create a mouthwatering dish that\'s sure to impress.','kerala-style-mutton-biryani',NULL,NULL,'indian','winter-special','everyday-meal','dinner,lunch','<ul>\r\n  <li>750 grams mutton, cut into 1 inch pieces on bone</li>\r\n   <li>1½ cups Daawat Dubar Basmati Rice</li>\r\n   <li>Salt to taste</li>\r\n   <li>5 tablespoons oil</li>\r\n   <li>2 star anise</li>\r\n   <li>6 bay leaves</li>\r\n   <li>8 green cardamoms</li>\r\n   <li>1 black cardamom</li>\r\n   <li>½ inch cinnamon</li>\r\n   <li>26-30 black peppercorns</li>\r\n   <li>1½ teaspoons caraway seeds (shahi jeera)</li>\r\n   <li>2 medium onions, finely chopped</li>\r\n   <li>1 tablespoons fennel seeds (saunf)</li>\r\n   <li>6-8 cloves</li>\r\n   <li>1 blade mace (javitri)</li>\r\n   <li>2 green chillies</li>\r\n   <li>2 tablespoons ginger-garlic-green chilli-poppy seeds paste</li>\r\n   <li>¼ teaspoon turmeric powder</li>\r\n   <li>3 tablespoons yogurt</li>\r\n   <li>1 tablespoon ghee</li>\r\n   <li>2 medium onions, sliced</li>\r\n   <li>1 cup coconut milk</li>\r\n   <li>1 tablespoon garam masala powder + as required</li>\r\n   <li>8-10 cashewnuts, halved and roasted</li>\r\n   <li>1 tablespoon raisins</li>\r\n   <li>½ tablespoon lemon juice</li>\r\n   <li>Whole wheat flour (atta) dough as required</li>\r\n   <li>6 tablespoons fried onions + for garnishing</li>\r\n   <li>1 tablespoon saffron milk</li>\r\n   <li>Ginger strips for garnishing</li>\r\n   <li>Fresh mint sprig for garnishing</li>\r\n  \r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n <li><span>Step 1</span> Marinate the mutton pieces with some salt.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 2</span> Heat 2 tbsps of oil in a deep non-stick pan. Add 1 star anise, 5 bay leaves, 4 green cardamoms, black cardamom, cinnamon, 16-18 peppercorns, 1 tsp caraway seeds, and chopped onions. Now mix and sauté till onions turn translucent.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 3</span> Grind together the remaining star anise, fennel seeds, remaining bay leaf, remaining green cardamoms, cloves, remaining peppercorns, mace, and the remaining caraway seeds to a fine powder.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 4</span> Add mutton pieces and broken green chillies to the pan, mix well, then cover and cook for 3-4 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 5</span> Add ginger-garlic-green chili-poppy seeds paste, turmeric powder, salt and yogurt. Mix well, then cover and cook till the mixture dries.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 6</span> Heat the remaining oil and ghee in another deep non-stick pan. Add sliced onions and sauté until translucent.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 7</span> Add Daawat Dubar Basmati Rice and 2½ tbsps ground powder, and mix well. Add 2 cups of water, coconut milk, and salt to taste, and again mix well. Add some ladles of stock from the mutton and stir lightly.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 8</span> Add garam masala powder to the mutton, mix well, cover, and continue to cook.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 9</span> Add cashew nuts, raisins, and lemon juice to the rice. Cover and cook till the rice is 3/4th done.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 10</span> Roll out wheat flour dough into a cylinder and place on a lid.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 11</span> Spread a layer of rice on the mutton pieces, then top with 3 tbsps fried onions and some garam masala powder. Spread another layer of the remaining rice on top, and add saffron milk and the remaining fried onions. Place a lid with dough on top and press. Cook on low heat for 25-30 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 12</span> Garnish with fried onions, ginger strips,, and mint sprig and serve hot.</li>\r\n</ul>','<div><br></div>','<div><br></div>','daawat-biryani-rice','2021-12-30 18:13:20','2024-04-26 12:21:29'),(26,'Hyderabadi Chicken Biryani',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'<p>1</p>','<p>1</p>',NULL,'2','1','2','NonVeg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/29-hyderabadi-chicken-biryani-1655094075.png','media/recipes/thumbnail/29-hyderabadi-chicken-biryani-1655094075.png','2021-12-24','Transforming your Daawat Basmati Rice into a lip-smacking Biryani is extremely simple, and this recipe will show you how!','Easy','50-55-minutes','5 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=T4-Gu1QgIQI&list=PLd4iYbCmUGHSF5VVs4eOPfVhKdVcSPCWn&index=12&t=27s',1,'Hyderabadi Chicken Biryani Recipe | Authentic Taste - Daawat','hyderabadi chicken biryani recipe','Experience the royal flavors of Hyderabadi cuisine with Daawat\'s authentic Hyderabadi Chicken Biryani Recipe. A perfect blend of spices, tender chicken, and aromatic rice, this recipe promises to deliver the classic taste and aroma of Hyderabad in every spoonful.','hyderabadi-chicken-biryani',NULL,NULL,'indian','always-loved','party,everyday-meal,festival','party','<ul>\r\n<li>750 grams chicken, cut into 2 inch pieces on the bone</li>\r\n<li>1½ cups of Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice, soaked</li>\r\n<li>6 green cardamoms</li>\r\n<li>2 black cardamoms</li>\r\n<li>1 blade mace (javitri)</li>\r\n<li>1 inch cinnamon</li>\r\n<li>6-8 cloves</li>\r\n<li>8-10 black peppercorns</li>\r\n<li>1 star anise (phool chakri)</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp caraway seeds (shahi jeera)</li>\r\n<li>Salt to taste</li>\r\n<li>1½ tbsps ginger-garlic paste</li>\r\n<li>2-3 green chillies, finely chopped</li>\r\n<li>1 cup yogurt</li>\r\n<li>¾ cup + 6 tb fried onions + for garnishing</li>\r\n<li>12-16 fresh mint leaves + as required</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp red chili powder</li>\r\n<li>½ tsp turmeric powder</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp garam masala powder + as required</li>\r\n<li>3 tbsps dried rose petals</li>\r\n<li>5 tbsps ghee + as required</li>\r\n<li>Whole wheat flour (atta) dough as required</li>\r\n<li>2 green chillies</li>\r\n<li>1 inch ginger, cut into strips</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsps saffron milk</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li><span>Step 1</span> Soak your Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice in sufficient water for 30 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 2</span> Take a piece of muslin cloth. Add 6 green cardamoms, 2 black cardamoms, mace, cinnamon, 6-8 cloves, 8-10 peppercorns, staranise, and ½ tsp caraway seeds, and tie it all into a potli.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 3</span> Heat 3 cups of water in a deep non-stick pan. Add potli and salt, cover, and bring to a boil.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 4</span> Put chicken pieces in a bowl. Add ginger-garlic paste, chopped green chillies, remaining caraway seeds, yogurt, ¾ cup fried onions, 12-16 mint leaves, chili powder, turmeric powder, 1 tsp garam masala powder, and 1 tbsp dried rose petals. Mix well and then set aside to marinate.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 5</span> Add drained Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice to boiling water, cover and cook till the rice is ¾th done.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 6</span> Add salt to the chicken pieces and mix well.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 7</span> Heat 3 tbsps of ghee in another deep non-stick pan. Add chicken pieces with the marinade.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 8</span> Roll out wheat flour dough into a cylinder and place on a lid.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 9</span> Break green chillies and add to the chicken, mix well and cook on high heat for 3-4 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 10</span> Discard the potli and strain the Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice in a colander. Add 2 tbsps of ghee to the Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice and mix well.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 11</span> Transfer some chicken pieces into a bowl and set aside.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 12</span> Spread a layer of strained Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice on the chicken pieces in the pan. Top with 3 tbsps fried onions, 1 tbsp dried rose petals, half the ginger strips, some garam masala powder, some mint leaves, and 1 tbsp saffron milk.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 13</span> Add the reserved chicken pieces on top and spread a layer of remaining strained Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice. Top with 3 tbsps fried onions, 1 tbsp dried rose petals, remaining ginger strips, some mint leaves, some ghee, remaining saffron milk, and some garam masala powder. Place the lid with dough on top and press. Cook on low heat for 20 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 14</span> Garnish with fried onions and mint leaves, and serve hot.</li>\r\n  \r\n</ul>','<div><br></div>','<div><br></div>','daawat-biryani-rice','2021-12-31 10:45:42','2024-04-26 11:57:24'),(27,'Vegetable Pulav',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2','2','2','Veg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/03-vegetable-pulav-1654853140.png','media/recipes/thumbnail/03-vegetable-pulav-1654843490.jpg','2022-06-10','A spicy dish prepared with colorful veggies and aromatic spices, Vegetable Pulav is perfect for your mid-day cravings. Cooked with Daawat Pulav Basmati’s long-grain rice, this dish becomes even more delicious and special!','Easy','30-min','2 People',NULL,NULL,'https://youtu.be/5EjnMgMF5fI',1,'Vegetable Pulav Recipe | Easy & Flavorful - Daawat','vegetable pulav recipe','Craft a deliciously aromatic Vegetable Pulav using Daawat\'s special recipe. Perfect for a wholesome meal, this easy-to-make dish brings the goodness of fresh veggies and rich spices, making every bite a celebration.','vegetable-pulav',NULL,NULL,'fusion,indian','all-time','everyday-meal','dinner,lunch','<ul>\r\n<li>1½  cups of Daawat Pulav Specialist Basmati Rice</li>\r\n<li>Water</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsps ghee</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp cumin seeds</li>\r\n<li>4-5 cloves</li>\r\n<li>5-6 peppercorns</li>\r\n<li>2-3 cardamoms</li>\r\n<li>1 bay leaf</li>\r\n<li>1-inch cinnamon stick</li>\r\n<li>2-3 green chillies</li>\r\n<li>1 carrot (diced)</li>\r\n<li>10-12 cauliflower florets</li>\r\n<li>5-6 french beans</li>\r\n<li>¼ cups of green peas</li>\r\n<li>Salt to taste</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li><span>Step 1</span> Pour 1½ cups of Daawat Pulav Specialist Basmati Rice in a big bowl. Wash the rice thoroughly with sufficient water at least 2-3 times.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 2</span> Add some more water and let the rice soak in the bowl for 20-25 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 3</span> On low or medium flame, heat 2 to 3 tbsps of oil or ghee in a deep pan</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 4</span> Add cumin seeds, cloves, black peppercorns, green cardamoms, bay leaf, and the cinnamon stick.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 5</span> Sauté the spices until the oil becomes fragrant, or until you hear a crackling sound.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 6</span> Pour the boiled Daawat Pulav Specialist Basmati Rice, and add salt to taste. Add water, cover the lid, and cook the rice on high flame for about 8-10 minutes. Subsequently cook the rice on low heat for about 5-6 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 7</span> Switch the heat off and allow it to rest for 10-15 minutes</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 8</span> Serve the dish hot with your choice of sauce.</li>\r\n</ul>',NULL,NULL,'daawat-pulav-rice','2022-06-10 12:14:50','2024-04-26 11:56:36'),(28,'Paneer Biryani Cups',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2','2','2','Veg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/04-paneer-biryani-cups-1654853126.png','media/recipes/thumbnail/04-paneer-biryani-cups-1654844435.jpg','2022-06-10','Cook a unique and delicious biryani with the world\'s longest grain: the Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice. This treat will not only satiate your hunger but also impress your guests!','Easy','30-min','2 People',NULL,NULL,'https://youtu.be/1FkT8-XNxzw',1,'Paneer Biryani Cups Recipe | Flavorful & Easy - Daawat','paneer biryani cups recipe','Dive into the delightful and easy Paneer Biryani Cups Recipe, a creative twist on traditional biryani. Perfect for parties and gatherings, these flavorful cups are a hit at any table. Visit Daawat for the full recipe.','paneer-biryani-cups',NULL,NULL,'fusion,indian','always-loved','party','party','<ul>\r\n<li>2 cups of Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice</li>\r\n<li>Salt to taste</li>\r\n<li>1 bay leaf</li>\r\n<li>1 star anise</li>\r\n<li>3-4 cloves</li>\r\n<li>1-inch cinnamon stick</li>\r\n<li>1 javitri</li>\r\n<li>2-3 green cardamom</li>\r\n<li>1 lemon wedge</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp ghee</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp fresh coriander</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsp butter</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp oil</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp jeera</li>\r\n<li>1 medium-sized onion</li>\r\n<li>4-5 medium-sized tomatoes</li>\r\n<li>6-7 garlic cloves</li>\r\n<li>1-inch ginger</li>\r\n<li>3-4 Kashmiri red chilies</li>\r\n<li>8-10 cashew nuts</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp red chili powder </li>\r\n<li>½ tbsp turmeric powder</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp sugar</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp garam masala</li>\r\n<li>500ml water</li>\r\n<li>½ Curd</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsps fresh cream</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp Kasturi methi</li>\r\n<li>¼ cup fried onions</li>\r\n<li>Paneer cubes 500gm</li>\r\n\r\n<li>For garnishing- </li>\r\n\r\n<li>1 tsp saffron infused milk</li>\r\n<li>Fried onions</li>\r\n<li>Fresh coriander</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n <li><span>Step 1</span> Add 2 cups of Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice in a bowl. Rinse thoroughly and soak them in water for 30 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 2</span> Take a pan and boil water in it. After boiling, add salt as required, along with 1 bay leaf, 1-star anise, 2-4 cloves, 1-inch cinnamon stick, 1 javitri, 2-3 green cardamoms, 1 lemon wedge, 1 tbsp ghee, 1 fresh coriander, and the 2 cups of drained Daawat Biryani Rice. Stir them well.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 3</span> Cook rice in boiling water until ¾th done.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 4</span> Meanwhile add 2 tbsps of butter, 1 tbsp of oil, and 1 tsp of jeera to another pan. Sauté them well.\r\n</li><li><span>Step 5</span> Now add 1 medium-sized onion, 3-4 medium-sized tomatoes, 6-7 garlic cloves, 1-inch ginger, 3-4 Kashmiri red chilies, 8-10 cashew nuts, 1 tbsp red chili powder, ½ tbsp turmeric powder, 1 tbsp sugar, 1 tbsp garam masala, salt to taste, and 500 ml water. Let it cook for 8-10 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 6</span> Grind it into a fine puree.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 7</span> Add 2 tbsps of fresh cream, 1 tbsp of Kasturi methi, and ¼th cup of fried onion. Stir it properly.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 8</span> Add 500 gm of paneer cubes and mix them well.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 9</span> Adjust salt to taste and serve by filling a mug halfway with a paneer makhani base and cooking the Basmati rice until the mug is almost full.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 10</span> Add saffron-infused milk, fried onions, and fresh coriander on the top to add to the taste.</li>\r\n</ul>',NULL,NULL,'daawat-biryani-rice','2022-06-10 12:30:35','2024-04-26 12:42:44'),(29,'Quick Mutton Biryani',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2','2','2','NonVeg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/05-quick-mutton-biryani-1654853111.png','media/recipes/thumbnail/05-quick-mutton-biryani-1654849811.png','2022-06-10','The flavorful and aromatic Mutton Biryani is a beautiful blend of the finest basmati - Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice, layered with broth, rich gravy, and zesty spices.','Easy','40-45-minutes','2 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=drKnP4WCY9k',1,'Delicious Quick Mutton Recipe | Savory & Speedy - Daawat','quick mutton recipe','Indulge in a mouthwatering Quick Mutton Recipe, the perfect blend of flavors for a fast, satisfying meal. Make this savory dish tonight with Daawat\'s easy guide.','quick-mutton-recipe',NULL,NULL,'mughlai,indian','all-time','weekend-meal','party,dinner,lunch','<ul>\r\n<li>1½ cups Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice</li>\r\n<li>Water</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsp oil</li>\r\n<li>2 onions</li>\r\n<li>1½ tbsp ginger-garlic paste</li>\r\n<li>2-3 green chilies</li>\r\n<li>2 tomatoes</li>\r\n<li>Salt</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsps coriander</li>\r\n<li>¼ cup browned onions</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp red chili powder</li>\r\n<li>¼ tbsp turmeric powder</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp biryani masala</li>\r\n<li>750 gms mutton, boiled</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp caraway seeds</li>\r\n<li>1 black cardamom</li>\r\n<li>3-4 cloves</li>\r\n<li>2-3 green cardamoms</li>\r\n<li>1-inch cinnamon stick</li>\r\n<li>1 bay leaf</li>\r\n<li>Coriander</li>\r\n<li>Mint</li>\r\n<li>1-inch ginger</li>\r\n<li>2-3 green chilies</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp ghee</li>\r\n<li>1-2 tbsps browned onions</li>\r\n<li>Papad</li>\r\n<li>Cucumber</li>\r\n<li>Tomato</li>\r\n<li>Beetroot raita</li>\r\n<li>Fried Cashew nuts</li>\r\n<li>Fried raisin</li>\r\n<li>Fresh pomegranate pearls</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li><span>Step 1</span> Wash Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice with water 2-3 times.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 2</span> After washing, soak the rice in sufficient water for 20-25 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 3</span> Take a pan and add 2 tbsps of oil to it.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 4</span> Add 2 chopped onions.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 5</span> Sauté them well until it becomes translucent.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 6</span> Add 1/1/2 ginger-garlic paste and sauté for 1-2 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 7</span> After this, add green chilies as required and mix till it achieves a golden color.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 8</span> Add 2 chopped tomatoes and salt to taste. Cook till the tomatoes become soft and pulpy.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 9</span> Then add 2 tbsps of coriander, ¼ cup of browned onions, 1 tbsp of red chili, ¼ tbsp of turmeric powder, and 1 tbsp of biryani masala. Sauté them for 1-2 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 10</span> Now, add 750gms of boiled mutton into it and let it cook for some time.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 11</span> Meanwhile, take another pan and boil water. Add salt as required, along with 1 tbsp of caraway seeds, 1 black cardamom, 3-4 cloves,  2-3 green cardamoms, 1-inch cinnamon stick, 1 bay leaf, and the drained rice. Cook till ¾ done.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 12</span> Add a layer of rice on top of the mutton and garnish it with coriander, mint, 1-inch ginger, 2-3 green chilies, 1 tbsp of ghee, and 1-2 tbsps of browned onions. Wrap the lid with foil paper.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 13</span> Cook on medium heat for 20-25 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 14</span> Switch off the heat and let the biryani rest for 10-15 minutes</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 15</span> Serve it hot with papad, tomato, cucumber, beetroot raita, mint, fried cashew nut and raisins, fresh pomegranate, and browned onions.</li>\r\n</ul>',NULL,NULL,'daawat-biryani-rice','2022-06-10 12:58:58','2024-04-26 12:48:20'),(30,'Kashmiri Pulav',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2','2','2','Veg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/06-kashmiri-pulav-1654853093.png','media/recipes/thumbnail/06-kashmiri-pulav-1654850225.jpg','2022-06-10','A traditional Kashmiri delicacy made with the aromatic, long-grained Daawat Pulav Basmati Rice, Kashmiri Pulav is a delight for the taste buds! \r\nA mix of zesty spices and exotic nuts, it’s perfect for a delicious meal with friends and family.','Easy','30-min','2 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H6YSP_UrXsY',1,'Kashmiri Pulav Recipe | Fragrant & Flavorful - Daawat','kashmiri pulav recipe','Unveil the essence of Kashmir with Daawat\'s Kashmiri Pulav Recipe. A luxurious blend of aromatic spices, succulent dry fruits, and perfectly cooked Basmati rice. Make every occasion special.','kashmiri-pulav',NULL,NULL,'kashmiri,indian','always-loved','weekend-meal,party,everyday-meal,festival','party,dinner,lunch','<ul>\r\n<li>1½&nbsp; Cups of Daawat Pulav Specialist Basmati Rice</li>\r\n<li>Water</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsps ghee</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp cumin seeds</li>\r\n<li>2 black cardamoms</li>\r\n<li>2 green cardamoms</li>\r\n<li>2-3 cloves</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp fennel seeds</li>\r\n<li>1 bay leaf</li>\r\n<li>1-inch cinnamon stick</li>\r\n<li>5-6 cashew nuts</li>\r\n<li>2 tsps raisins</li>\r\n<li>Cottage cheese (150 g)</li>\r\n<li>½ tsp dried ginger powder</li>\r\n<li>¼ tsp asafoetida</li>\r\n<li>½ cup of milk</li>\r\n<li>Fresh pomegranate seeds</li>\r\n<li>Salt to taste</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li><span>Step 1</span> Pour 1½ cup of Daawat Pulav Specialist Basmati Rice into a big bowl. Wash the rice thoroughly with sufficient water at least 2-3 times.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 2</span> Add some more water and let the rice soak in the bowl for 20-25 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 3</span> On low or medium flame, heat 2 to 3 tbsps of oil or ghee in a deep pan.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 4</span> Add cumin seeds, black cardamom seeds, cloves, fennel seeds, bay leaf, and cinnamon stick to the heated oil.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 5</span> Sauté the spices until the oil becomes fragrant, or until you hear a crackling sound.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 6</span> Add 5-6 cashew nuts, raisins, and cottage cheese cubes to the mix and sauté.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 7</span> Next, add dried garlic powder and asafoetida to the mix and stir well.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 8</span> Pour the boiled Daawat Pulav Specialist Basmati Rice, water, milk, and salt to taste.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 9</span> Cover with a lid and let it cook on medium heat for 10-12 minutes. Switch off the heat and let it rest for 15 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 10</span> Garnish with fresh pomegranate seeds and serve hot.</li>\r\n    \r\n</ul>',NULL,NULL,'daawat-pulav-rice','2022-06-10 14:07:05','2024-04-26 12:36:58'),(31,'Paneer Dum Biryani',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2','2','2','Veg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/07-dum-paneer-biryani-1654853081.png','media/recipes/thumbnail/07-dum-paneer-biryani-1654851185.png','2022-06-10','Cook the delicious Paneer Makhani Dum Biryani, a dish with succulent cottage cheese cubes dipped in gravy and mixed with the finest basmati rice - Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice! All in all the perfect dinner, or just for whenever you’re craving something slightly rich!','Easy','30-min','2 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4VrSecohZ_A',1,'Paneer Dum Biryani Recipe for a Royal Feast - Daawat','paneer dum biryani recipe','Indulge in the rich flavors of our Paneer Dum Biryani Recipe. Perfect for any occasion, this dish will leave you craving more. Visit Daawat for the complete recipe.','paneer-dum-biryani',NULL,NULL,'fusion,indian','all-time','weekend-meal,everyday-meal','party,dinner,lunch','<ul>\r\n<li>2 Cups Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice</li>\r\n<li>3L boiling water</li>\r\n<li>Salt</li>\r\n<li>1 bay leaf</li>\r\n<li>1 star anise</li>\r\n<li>3-4 cloves</li>\r\n<li>1-inch cinnamon stick</li>\r\n<li>1 javitri</li>\r\n<li>2-3 green cardamom</li>\r\n<li>1 lemon wedge</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp ghee</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp fresh coriander</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsp butter</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp oil</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp jeera</li>\r\n<li>1 medium sized onion</li>\r\n<li>4-5 medium sized tomatoes</li>\r\n<li>6-7 garlic cloves</li>\r\n<li>1 ginger</li>\r\n<li>3-4 Kashmiri red chillies</li>\r\n<li>8-10 cashew nuts</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp red chili powder</li>\r\n<li>½ tbsp turmeric powder</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp sugar</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp garam masala</li>\r\n<li>½ cup curd</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsp fresh cream</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp Kasuri methi</li>\r\n<li>1/4th cup fried onions</li>\r\n<li>500 gms paneer cubes</li>\r\n<li>Live charcoal</li>\r\n   \r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n <li><span>Step 1</span> Take the Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice in a bowl. Add sufficient water and rinse  2-3 times</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 2</span> Add fresh water and soak for 30 minutes. Drain the water.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 3</span> Boil 3L of water in a deep non-stick pan. Add salt, bay leaf, star anise, cloves, cinnamon stick, javitri, green cardamoms, lemon wedge, ghee, and fresh coriander. Add the soaked rice, mix, and cook until the rice is ¾ done. Drain the rice.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 4</span> In a pan add butter, oil, and jeera, and then stir.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 5</span> Now add onion, tomatoes, garlic cloves, ginger, Kashmiri red chili, cashew nuts, red chili powder, turmeric powder, sugar, garam masala, and salt to taste. Add 500 ml of water and give it a good mix.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 6</span> Let it cook for 8-10 minutes and then grind it into a fine puree.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 7</span> Then add curd, fresh cream, Kasuri methi, fried onions, and paneer cubes to this puree. Finally, add salt to taste.\r\n</li><li><span>Step 8</span> Take another dish and add ghee to the bottom, then add a layer of paneer. Top it off with fresh coriander and fried onions. Then add a layer of rice on top of it.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 9</span> Add a second layer of paneer on top of the rice and garnish with fried onions. Then add a second layer of rice. Sprinkle some fresh coriander, fried onions, and ghee.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 10</span> Seal the vessel with dough and set it over the tawa on a low flame. Cook on dum for 15-20 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 11</span> Finally add live charcoal and ghee, and then cover and smoke the biryani for 3-4 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 12</span> Serve hot with curd.</li>\r\n</ul>',NULL,NULL,'daawat-biryani-rice','2022-06-10 14:23:05','2024-04-26 12:45:33'),(32,'Egg Biryani',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2','2','2','NonVeg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/08-egg-biryani-1654853036.png','media/recipes/thumbnail/08-egg-biryani-1654853036.png','2022-06-10','Are you an egg lover? Then this is for you!\r\nA wholesome one-pot meal prepared with aromatic Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice, hard-boiled eggs and topped with veggies.','Easy','40-45-minutes','2 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1ubL50kkNsY',1,'Egg Biryani Recipe: Quick & Delicious - Daawat','egg biryani recipe','Discover the perfect Egg Biryani Recipe by Daawat. A delightful combination of fluffy rice, aromatic spices, and eggs. Quick, easy, and irresistibly tasty, it\'s the ultimate meal for any occasion.','egg-biryani',NULL,NULL,'mughlai,fusion,indian','always-loved','weekend-meal,party,everyday-meal','party,dinner,lunch','<ul>\r\n<li>8 eggs (anda), hard-boiled and peeled</li>\r\n<li>1½ cups Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice, soaked for 30 minutes and drained</li>\r\n<li>4 tbsps oil</li>\r\n<li>1 black cardamom</li>\r\n<li>½ inch cinnamon</li>\r\n<li>1 bay leaf</li>\r\n<li>18 cloves</li>\r\n<li>12-16 black peppercorns</li>\r\n<li>9 green cardamoms</li>\r\n<li>1 large onion, finely chopped</li>\r\n<li>4 medium potatoes, boiled and peeled</li>\r\n<li>Salt to taste</li>\r\n<li>Juice of ½ lemon</li>\r\n<li>½ tsp turmeric powder</li>\r\n<li>2 tsps red chili powder</li>\r\n<li>1½ tbsps ginger-garlic paste</li>\r\n<li>3 green chilies</li>\r\n<li>¾ cup fresh tomato puree</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsps coriander powder</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp + a pinch of garam masala powder</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp chopped fresh coriander leaves</li>\r\n<li>¼ cup yogurt</li>\r\n<li>3 tbsps of fried onions + a few fresh mint leaves for garnishing</li>\r\n<li>1-inch ginger, cut into strips</li>\r\n<li>Fresh mint sprig for garnishing</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li><span>Step 1</span> Heat 2 tbsps of oil in a deep non-stick pan.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 2</span> Heat 3 cups of water in another deep non-stick pan. Add 1 black cardamom, ½ inch cinnamon, 1 bay leaf, 8 of the cloves, black peppercorns, and 4 green cardamoms to the water. Bring the whole thing to a boil.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 3</span> Add remaining cloves and remaining green cardamoms to the oil and sauté till fragrant.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 4</span> Add the Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice to the boiling water and let it cook.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 5</span> Add onions to the oil and sauté until translucent.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 6</span> Cut the potatoes into cubes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 7</span> Add salt, 1 tbsp oil, and lemon juice to the Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice and cook till ¾th done.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 8</span> Add ¼ tsp turmeric powder and 1½ tsps chili powder to the onions and mix well. Now add eggs and potato cubes to it, and fry for a minute. Transfer the eggs and potatoes to a bowl and set aside.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 9</span> Add the ginger-garlic paste and mix. Then add green chilies, tomato puree, and salt. Mix it all well and cook for 2-3 minutes.\r\n</li><li><span>Step 10</span> Strain the Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice in a colander and set it aside.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 11</span> Add coriander powder, remaining chili powder, 1 tbsp garam masala powder, and the remaining turmeric powder to the tomato puree mixture. Mix it well and cook till the oil separates.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 12</span> Add the fried eggs (anda), potato cubes, coriander leaves, and yogurt, and spread a layer of strained Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice on top.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 13</span> Top it with fried onions, some mint leaves, a pinch of garam masala powder, and ginger strips. Add the remaining oil, then cover and cook on medium heat for 20 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 14</span> Finally, garnish with fried onions and mint sprig, and serve hot.</li>\r\n  \r\n</ul>',NULL,NULL,'daawat-biryani-rice','2022-06-10 14:53:56','2024-04-26 12:20:51'),(33,'Mutton Dum Biryani',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2','2','2','NonVeg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/09-dum-mutton-biryani--1654853784.png','media/recipes/thumbnail/09-dum-mutton-biryani--1654853784.jpg','2022-06-10','With a new beginning, you need a dish as special as this to brighten up your dinner table. Cue Mutton Dum Biryani- a delicacy with succulent meat cooked in rich gravy and spices accompanied by the finest Daawat Basmati Rice. Sounds like a delight? Wait till you taste it!','Easy','50-55-minutes','3 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Hci8BW3Xz2E&feature=youtu.be',1,'Mutton Dum Biryani Recipe | Slow Cooked Perfection - Daawat','mutton dum biryani recipe','Master the art of making Mutton Dum Biryani with Daawat\'s authentic recipe. Savour every bite of this richly flavored, slow-cooked delicacy that promises an unforgettable dining experience.','mutton-dum-biryani',NULL,NULL,'mughlai,fusion,indian','all-time','weekend-meal,party','party,dinner,lunch','<ul>\r\n   <li>1-kilogram mutton, cut into 2-inch pieces on the bone</li>\r\n<li>2 cups Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice</li>\r\n<li>4-5 small potatoes, cut into 1-inch pieces</li>\r\n<li>Salt to taste</li>\r\n<li>1½ tsp red chili powder</li>\r\n<li>¼ tsp turmeric powder</li>\r\n<li>1½ tsps garam masala powder</li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;¾ cup browned onions + for garnish</li>\r\n<li>4-5 tbsps melted ghee + for drizzling</li>\r\n<li>1-2 tbsps dried rose petals + for sprinkling</li>\r\n<li>1½ tbsps ginger-garlic paste</li>\r\n<li>4-5 tbsps chopped fresh coriander leaves</li>\r\n<li>15-20 fresh mint leaves + for garnish</li>\r\n<li>2 medium onions, thinly sliced</li>\r\n<li>1 cup whisked yogurt</li>\r\n<li>8-10 black peppercorns</li>\r\n<li>4-5 cloves</li>\r\n<li>3 green cardamoms</li>\r\n<li>2 black cardamoms</li>\r\n<li>2-inch cinnamon stick</li>\r\n<li>1 bay leaf</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp caraway seeds (shahi jeera)</li>\r\n<li>A large pinch of saffron, soaked in 1 tbsp warm milk</li>\r\n<li>1-inch ginger, cut into thin strips</li>\r\n<li>2-3 green chilies, slit</li>\r\n<li>2 tsp screwpine water (kewra)</li>\r\n<li>2 tsp rose water</li>\r\n<li>2 tsp lemon juice</li>\r\n<li>Ready-made whole wheat dough for sealing</li>\r\n<li>Yogurt to serve</li>\r\n<li>Salad to serve</li>\r\n<li> Papads to serve</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n  <li><span>Step 1</span> Take mutton in a large bowl, add the potatoes, salt, red chili powder, turmeric powder, garam masala powder, browned onions, 2-3 tbsps melted ghee, dried rose petals, ginger-garlic paste, 2-3 tbsps coriander leaves, and 10-15 mint leaves. Now mix until well combined, and set aside to marinate for 45-50 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 2</span> Take the Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice in a bowl. Add sufficient water and wash 2-3 times.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 3</span> Add sufficient water and soak for 20-25 minutes. Drain the water.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 4</span> Heat remaining melted ghee in a non-stick deep pan and sauté on high heat for 2-3 minutes, or till golden brown.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 5</span> Add the marinated mutton and sauté on high heat for 10-15 minutes while stirring in between every few minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 6</span> Add the yogurt and mix well. Continue to sauté for 4-5 minutes. Now cover and cook on medium heat, stirring continuously at regular intervals till the mutton is ¾ done.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 7</span> Meanwhile, heat sufficient water in another deep pan. Add salt, black peppercorns, cloves, green cardamoms, cinnamon sticks, bay leaf, and caraway seeds.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 8</span> Add the soaked rice and mix. Cook till the rice is ¾ done.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 9</span> Drain the rice and evenly spread it over the mutton mixture. Drizzle ghee-soaked saffron, and add ginger strips and green chilies. Sprinkle remaining coriander leaves, remaining mint leaves, dried rose petals, kewra¸ and rose water, and then drizzle lemon juice.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 10</span> Press the whole wheat dough onto the edges of the pan. Place a lid over it to seal.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 11</span> Keep a Tawa on heat. Place the pan over it and cook on medium heat for 15-20 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 12</span> Switch the heat off and allow it to rest for 15 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 13</span> Discard the whole wheat dough and transfer the biryani to a serving plate. Garnish with browned onion and fresh mint leaves. Finally, serve hot with yogurt, salad, and papads!</li>\r\n    \r\n</ul>',NULL,NULL,'daawat-biryani-rice','2022-06-10 15:06:24','2024-04-26 12:22:06'),(34,'Paneer Biryani',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2','2','2','Veg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/10-paneer-biryani-1654853947.png','media/recipes/thumbnail/10-paneer-biryani-1654853947.png','2022-06-10','Did you say- a perfect meal? We heard Paneer Biryani! \r\nA dish where long-grained basmati rice is cooked to perfection, blended with authentic Indian herbs and soft paneer pieces to create a delightful taste experience.','Easy','40-45-minutes','2 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vh-5pFYvfqQ&feature=youtu.be',1,'Paneer Biryani Recipe | Rich & Flavorful - Daawat','paneer biryani recipe','Enjoy the exquisite flavors of Paneer Biryani, a delectable recipe that combines fragrant Basmati rice, rich spices, and paneer. This dish is a vegetarian delight that promises an unforgettable culinary experience.','paneer-biryani',NULL,NULL,'fusion,indian','always-loved','weekend-meal,party,everyday-meal','party,dinner,lunch','<ul>\r\n<li>500 grams cottage cheese (paneer), cut into 1-inch cubes</li>\r\n<li>5½ cups Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice</li>\r\n<li>Salt to taste</li>\r\n<li>7-8 black peppercorns</li>\r\n<li>3-4 green cardamoms</li>\r\n<li>2-3 cloves</li>\r\n<li>2-3 tbsps ghee</li>\r\n<li>3-4 cloves</li>\r\n<li>6-8 black peppercorns</li>\r\n<li>2 green cardamoms</li>\r\n<li>1-2 bay leaves</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp cumin seeds</li>\r\n<li>2-3 green chilies, slit</li>\r\n<li>2 large onions, thinly sliced</li>\r\n<li>1½ tbsps ginger-garlic paste</li>\r\n<li>1 cup fresh tomato puree</li>\r\n<li>Salt to taste</li>\r\n<li>2 tsp red chili powder</li>\r\n<li>½ tsp turmeric powder</li>\r\n<li>¾ tsp coriander powder</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp cumin powder</li>\r\n<li>1½ tbsps biryani masala</li>\r\n<li>3 tbsps browned onions</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsps chopped fresh mint leaves</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp chopped fresh coriander leaves</li>\r\n<li>2-3 tsp butter</li>\r\n<li>2-3 tbsps yogurt</li>\r\n<li>A large pinch of saffron, soaked in 1-2 tbsps warm water</li>\r\n<li>2-3 tsp rose water</li>\r\n<li>1-2 tsp screwpine (kewra) water</li>\r\n<li>Ghee for drizzling</li>\r\n<li>¼ cup browned onions + for garnish</li>\r\n<li>12-15 fresh coriander sprigs</li>\r\n<li>10-12 fresh mint leaves</li>\r\n<li>2-3 green chilies, slit</li>\r\n<li>1-inch ginger, cut into thin strips</li>\r\n<li>1-2 tsp dried rose petals</li>\r\n<li>Fresh mint sprig for garnish</li>\r\n<li>Boondi raita as required</li>\r\n<li>Onion rings</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n <li><span>Step 1</span> Take Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice in a bowl. Add sufficient water and wash 2-3 times.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 2</span> Add fresh water and soak for 25-30 minutes. Drain the water.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 3</span> Boil 6-8 cups of water in a deep non-stick pan. Add salt, black peppercorns, green cardamoms, and cloves. Add the soaked rice, mix and cook for 10-15 minutes or till the rice is ¾ done. Drain the rice.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 4</span> To make the masala, heat ghee in a deep pan. Add cloves, black peppercorns, green cardamoms, bay leaves, cumin seeds, green chilies, and onions. Then sauté until golden brown.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 5</span> Add the ginger-garlic paste, mix, and cook for 1-2 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 6</span> Pour the tomato puree and mix well. Now add salt, and then mix and cook for 2-3 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 7</span> Add red chili powder, turmeric powder, coriander powder, cumin powder, biryani masala, browned onions, mint leaves, coriander leaves, and butter, and mix well. Cook on medium heat till the fat separates.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 8</span> Reduce the heat to low and add yogurt, then mix well. Add 1⁄2 cup water, mix, and cook for 3-4 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 9</span> Add the paneer cubes and gently mix till well combined. Evenly spread the cooked rice over the paneer masala. Drizzle soaked saffron, rose water, screwpine water, and ghee. Sprinkle browned onions, coriander sprigs, mint leaves, green chilies, ginger, and dried rose petals.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 10</span> Cover the pan with an aluminum foil and place the lid on it. Cook on low heat for 8-10 minutes. Now switch the heat off and transfer the paneer biryani to a serving plate.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 11</span> Garnish with browned onions, and mint sprig. Serve hot with boondi raita and onion rings.</li>\r\n    \r\n</ul>',NULL,NULL,'daawat-biryani-rice','2022-06-10 15:09:07','2024-04-26 12:41:09'),(35,'Veg Biryani',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2','2','2','Veg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/11-veg-biryani-1654856268.png','media/recipes/thumbnail/11-veg-biryani-1654856299.png','2022-06-10','Easy to make Vegetable Biryani recipe in Marathi by Sanjeev Kapoor. Know how to make scrumptious restaurant style vegetable biryani at home simply, step by step!','Easy','40-45-minutes','2 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hIQe1BAJFf8',1,'Veg Biryani Recipe: Aromatic and Flavorful - Daawat','veg biryani recipe','Discover the rich flavors of India with our Veg Biryani Recipe. A perfect mix of spices, veggies, and rice for a truly aromatic and delicious meal. Cook with Daawat today.','veg-biryani',NULL,NULL,'indian','all-time','weekend-meal,party,everyday-meal','party,dinner,lunch','<ul>\r\n<li>2 medium carrots, peeled and cut into diamonds</li>\r\n<li>10-12 cauliflower florets</li>\r\n<li>5-6 french beans, cut into pieces</li>\r\n<li>4-5 baby corns, cut into diamonds</li>\r\n<li>¼ cup green peas</li>\r\n<li>100 grams of cottage cheese (paneer), cut into small cubes</li>\r\n<li>1½ cups Daawat Super Basmati Rice, soaked for 30 minutes and drained</li>\r\n<li>4 tbsps ghee for drizzling and brushing</li>\r\n<li>1 inch cinnamon</li>\r\n<li>5 green cardamoms</li>\r\n<li>1 blade mace (javitri)</li>\r\n<li>10-12 cloves</li>\r\n<li>10-12 black peppercorns</li>\r\n<li>1 bay leaf</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp caraway seeds (shahi jeera)</li>\r\n<li>1 large onion, sliced</li>\r\n<li>2 green chillies</li>\r\n<li>1½ tbsps ginger-garlic paste</li>\r\n<li>¼ tsp turmeric powder</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp coriander-cumin powder</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp red chili powder</li>\r\n<li>½ cup fresh tomato puree</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsps fresh cream</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp chopped fresh coriander leaves</li>\r\n<li>4 tbsps fried onions</li>\r\n<li>Green cardamom powder for sprinklins</li>\r\n<li>1 inch ginger, cut into strips</li>\r\n<li>8-10 raisins</li>\r\n<li>8-10 cashew nuts, roasted</li>\r\n<li>Screwpine essence (kewra) for drizzling</li>\r\n<li>4 tsps saffron milk for brushing</li>\r\n<li>Few fresh mint leaves</li>\r\n<li>Refined flour (maida) or whole wheat flour (atta) roti for covering</li>\r\n   \r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n   <li> <span>Step 1</span> Heat Ghee In A Deep Non-Stick Deep Pan. Add Cinnamon, Green Cardamoms, Mace, Cloves, Peppercorns, And Bay Leaf, And Sauté Till Fragrant.</li>\r\n   <li> <span>Step 2</span> THeat Remaining Ghee In Another Deep Non-Stick Pan. Add Caraway Seeds And Sauté For A Minute.</li>\r\n   <li> <span>Step 3</span> Add Daawat Super Basmati Rice To The Sautéed Spices And Mix Well. Add 3 Cups of Hot Water.</li>\r\n   <li> <span>Step 4</span> Add Onions To Caraway Seeds, Mix, And Sauté Till Onions Turn Translucent.</li>\r\n   <li> <span>Step 5</span> Add Salt To The Rice, Cover, And Cook Till 3/4th Done. Strain And Set Aside.</li>\r\n   <li> <span>Step 6</span> Break Green Chillies, Add To Onions, Mix, And Sauté For A Minute. Add Ginger-Garlic Paste, Mix Well, And Sauté.</li>\r\n   <li> <span>Step 7</span> Add Turmeric Powder, Coriander-Cumin Powder, and Chili Powder, And Mix Well. Add Tomato Puree, Mix Well, And Cook For 1-2 Minutes.</li>\r\n   <li> <span>Step 8</span> Add Carrots, Cauliflower, French Beans, and Baby Corn And Mix. Add Salt And Cream And Mix Well. Add Coriander Leaves, Green Peas, And Cottage Cheese Cubes, Mix Lightly, And Cook For 3-4 Minutes.</li>\r\n   <li> <span>Step 9</span> Preheat Oven To 180º C.</li>\r\n   <li> <span>Step 10</span> Spread A Layer Of Cooked Vegetables In A Handi And Top With A Layer Of Strained Daawat Super Basmati Rice. Sprinkle 2 Tablespoons Fried Onions, Cardamom Powder, Half The Ginger Strips, Raisins, And Cashew Nuts. Drizzle Some Screwpine Essence, 2 Teaspoons Saffron Milk, Some Ghee, And Sprinkle Some Mint Leaves.</li>\r\n   <li> <span>Step 11</span> Top With A Layer Of Remaining Cooked Vegetables And Remaining Strained Daawat Super Basmati Rice. Sprinkle Some Cardamom Powder, Remaining Fried Onions, Remaining Ginger Strips, And Some Mint Leaves. Drizzle Some Screwpine Essence And Remaining Saffron Milk.</li>\r\n   <li> <span>Step 12</span> Cover The Handi With Roti, and Brush The Top With Some Ghee And Saffron Milk. Place The Handi In The Preheated Oven And Cook Till The Top Turns Reddish.</li>\r\n</ul>',NULL,NULL,'daawat-biryani-rice','2022-06-10 15:47:48','2024-04-26 12:49:11'),(36,'Egg Fried Rice',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2','2','2','NonVeg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/36-brown-rice-egg-biryani-1654856433.png','media/recipes/thumbnail/36-brown-rice-egg-biryani-1654856433.png','2022-06-10','Delicious, healthy & homemade Egg Fried Rice is here to relish your taste buds! Step by step, know how to keep your family’s health in check and treat your family with Daawat Brown Basmati Rice that cooks in just 15 minutes!','Easy','30-min','2 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=C96E0EDzCmI',1,'Egg Fried Rice Biryani Recipe | Quick & Delicious - Daawat','egg fried rice biryani recipe','Discover how to make Egg Fried Rice Biryani with Daawat\'s simple recipe. A delightful mix of flavors for a quick, nutritious, and mouth-watering meal option.','egg-fried-rice',NULL,NULL,'indian','all-time','everyday-meal','healthy','<ul>\r\n<li>2 cups Daawat Brown Basmati Rice</li>\r\n<li>2 eggs</li>\r\n<li>4 tbsp oil</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp chopped garlic</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp red chilies</li>\r\n<li>1/4th cup chopped spring onion</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp sugar</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp black pepper</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp soy sauce</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp vinegar</li>\r\n<li>Salt to taste</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li><span>Step 1</span> Rinse your Daawat Brown Basmati Rice 3-4 times with water.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 2</span> Put 3 liters of water to boil.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 3</span> Add 1 tbsp oil, salt to taste, and the rinsed rice to the boiling water.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 4</span> Cook until it’s 3/4th done, strain, and set the water and rice both aside.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 5</span> Now add 3 tbsp oil, chopped garlic, red chilies, and spring onions to a pan.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 6</span> Sauté for 2-3 minutes and then add the cooked rice to it.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 7</span> Now add sugar, black pepper, and salt to the mixture. Give it a quick stir.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 8</span> Then pour the soy sauce and vinegar into the rice and mix it well.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 9</span> Once appropriately mixed, make a cavity in the center and add your eggs.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 10</span> Scramble and cook.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 11</span> Now add 1/4th cup of that starchy rice water you kept aside in the beginning.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 12</span> Cook for a couple of minutes and then add it to a serving bowl.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 13</span> Top it off with some spring onion greens and you’re done!</li>\r\n</ul>',NULL,NULL,'daawat-brown-rice','2022-06-10 15:50:33','2024-04-26 12:26:14'),(37,'Brown Rice Khichdi',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2','2','2','Veg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/13-brown-rice-khichdi-1654856541.png','media/recipes/thumbnail/13-brown-rice-khichdi-1654856541.png','2022-06-10','For a healthier take on khichdi, add Daawat Brown Basmati Rice which is both flavorful and filled with fiber.\r\nFollow the simple steps, cook Brown Rice in just 15 minutes and enjoy this comfort food.','Easy','15-minu','1 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wIVXhcAGmfM&feature=youtu.be',1,'Brown Rice Khichdi Recipe | Healthy & Comforting - Daawat','brown rice khichdi recipe','Savor the goodness of Daawat\'s Brown Rice Khichdi Recipe, a nutritious and comforting meal perfect for any day. Made with wholesome brown rice and a medley of spices, this khichdi recipe is not only easy to digest but also packed with health benefits.','brown-rice-khichdi',NULL,NULL,'indian','all-time','everyday-meal','healthy','<ul>\r\n<li>½ cup Daawat Quick-Cooking Brown Basmati rice</li>\r\n<li>Water</li>\r\n<li>½ cup soaked split skinless green gram</li>\r\n<li>Salt</li>\r\n<li>½ tsp turmeric powder</li>\r\n<li>Ghee</li>\r\n<li>1 ½ tsp Cumin Seeds</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsp garlic</li>\r\n<li>½ tbsp ginger</li>\r\n<li>¼ tsp asafoetida</li>\r\n<li>2 green chilis</li>\r\n<li>Onions</li>\r\n<li>Tomatoes</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp red chili powder</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsp coriander</li>\r\n<li>1 coriander leaf</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n  <li><span>Step 1</span> Take ½ cup of the Daawat Quick-Cooking Brown Rice and add water to it. Rinse it 2-3 times and then soak it in fresh water for 25-30 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 2</span> Now add the rice to a cooker and add ½ cup soaked, split, skinless green gram, salt to taste, ½ tsp turmeric powder, and 4 ½ cups water. Cook for 5-6 whistles.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 3</span> Open the cooker once the pressure settles completely.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 4</span> Take a pan and add 2 tbsps of ghee, 1 ½ tsp of cumin seeds, 2 tbsps of garlic, ½ tbsp of ginger, ¼ tsp of asafoetida, and sauté for 30 seconds.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 5</span> Then add 2 cut-up green chilis to this mix, and stir.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 6</span> Now add freshly cut-up onions, and sauté till translucent.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 7</span> Add tomatoes and salt to taste, and cook until the mix is pulpy.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 8</span> Add 1 tbsp red chili powder, and stir again.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 9</span> Now add the cooked rice mixture to this mix, and stir well.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 10</span> Add ¾ cup of water and cook for another 2-3 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 11</span> Top it off with 2 tbsps of coriander, and stir.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 12</span> Your Brown Rice Khichdi is ready to serve. Put it in a bowl or a plate and layer with some ghee on top for that authentic taste. Add a coriander leaf to make it look attractive and you’re good to go!</li>\r\n</ul>',NULL,NULL,'daawat-brown-rice','2022-06-10 15:52:21','2024-04-26 12:19:58'),(38,'Brown Rice Pulao',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2','2','2','Veg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/14-brown-rice-pulao-1654856799.png','media/recipes/thumbnail/14-brown-rice-pulao-1654856824.jpg','2022-06-10','Treat your family to a healthy version of a classic pulav recipe by replacing your rice with Daawat Brown Rice! \r\nIt cooks in only 15 minutes, and is full of essential nutrients to make you feel strong and healthy!','Easy','15-minu','2 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xnP2ZQwV0n8',1,'Easy Brown Rice Recipe for Healthy Eating - Daawat','easy brown rice recipe','Unlock the secrets to cooking perfect brown rice every time. Our simple Brown Rice Recipe guarantees fluffy, nutritious grains. Visit Daawat for full details and more.','brown-rice',NULL,NULL,'indian','all-time','everyday-meal','healthy',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'daawat-brown-rice','2022-06-10 15:56:39','2024-04-26 12:44:46'),(39,'Mushroom Pulav',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2','2','2','Veg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/16-mushroom-pulav-1655092605.png','media/recipes/thumbnail/16-mushroom-pulav-1655092605.jpg','2022-06-13','Get the goodness of Mushrooms in your Pulav, along with flavorful spices and the aromatic, slender grains of Daawat Pulav Basmati, follow the recipe to create a scrumptious dish fit for a royal feast.','Easy','30-min','2 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1u8t7k5E3d4',1,'Delicious Mushroom Pulav Recipe | Quick & Easy - Daawat','mushroom pulav recipe','Master the art of making flavorful Mushroom Pulav with our easy-to-follow recipe. A perfect blend of spices and mushrooms awaits. Dive into the recipe on Daawat.','mushroom-pulav',NULL,NULL,'fusion,indian','all-time','weekend-meal,everyday-meal','dinner,lunch','<ul>\r\n<li>1 ½ cups of Daawat Pulav Basmati Rice</li>\r\n<li>Water</li>\r\n<li>4 shiitake mushrooms</li>\r\n<li>2 green cardamoms</li><li>6-8 black peppercorns</li>\r\n<li>2-3 cloves</li>\r\n<li>1 bay leaf</li>\r\n<li>Salt</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsps Oil</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp cumin seeds</li>\r\n<li>1 ½ tbsps garlic</li>\r\n<li>2 onions</li>\r\n<li>10-15 button mushrooms</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsps of toasted pine nuts</li>\r\n<li>¾ cup of fenugreek leaves</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n   <li> <span>Step 1</span> Take 1 ½ cups of Daawat Pulav Basmati Rice and wash it properly with water 2-3 times. Then soak it in fresh water for 30 minutes.</li>\r\n   <li> <span>Step 2</span> Put some water in a pan and put it on the stove, add 4 shiitake mushrooms, 2 green cardamoms, 6-8 black peppercorns, 2-3 cloves, 1 bay leaf, and salt to taste. Allow it to boil.\r\n   </li>\r\n   <li> <span>Step 3</span> Remove the shiitake mushrooms from this and slice them. Add the previously soaked rice to this mix and cook for 10 minutes.</li>\r\n   <li> <span>Step 4</span> Add 2 tbsps of oil in a pan along with 1 tsp cumin seeds, 1 ½ tbsps garlic, and saute till it\'s golden brown.\r\n   </li>\r\n   <li> <span>Step 5</span> Then add 2 onions and saute till the mix is translucent.\r\n   </li>\r\n   <li> <span>Step 6</span> Add 10-15 button mushrooms and the sliced shiitake mushrooms, 2 tbsps of toasted pine nuts, and saute for 4-5 minutes. Then add salt as per taste and mix it well.</li>\r\n   <li> <span>Step 7</span> Finally, add the rice and sprinkle it with ¾ cup of fenugreek leaves. Mix it all well and cook for 2-3 minutes and your mushroom pulav is ready to serve!</li>\r\n</ul>',NULL,NULL,'daawat-pulav-rice','2022-06-13 09:26:45','2024-04-26 12:46:09'),(40,'Lemon Brown Rice',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2','2','2','Veg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/17-lemon-brown-rice-1655092704.png','media/recipes/thumbnail/17-lemon-brown-rice-1655092704.jpg','2022-06-13','In the mood for something tangy? \r\nTry the Lemon Brown Rice, full of aromatic spices, and a splash of tangy lemon made with the healthy goodness of Daawat Brown Rice that cooks in just 15 mins!','Easy','15-minu','1 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jUCg2ozs9zM&feature=youtu.be',1,'Lemon Brown Rice Recipe | Zesty & Healthy - Daawat','lemon brown rice recipe','Master the art of cooking with our Lemon Brown Rice Recipe. Enjoy a healthy, delicious side dish that\'s perfect for any meal. Visit Daawat for the full recipe and tips.','lemon-brown-rice',NULL,NULL,'fusion,indian','always-loved','everyday-meal','healthy','<ul>\r\n<li>1 ½ cups of Daawat Brown Basmati Rice</li>\r\n<li>Water</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsps of coconut oil</li>\r\n<li>1 ½ tsps of split Bengal gram</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp of split skinless black gram</li>\r\n<li>½ tsp of asafoetida</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp of mustard seeds</li>\r\n<li>4 dried red chilis</li>\r\n<li>½ cup raw peanuts</li>\r\n<li>2 sprigs of curry leaves</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp lemon juice</li>\r\n<li>Coriander</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n   <li> <span>Step 1</span>&nbsp;Take 1 ½ cups of Daawat Quick Cooking Basmati Rice and wash it properly with water 2-3 times. Then soak it in fresh water for 30 minutes.</li>\r\n   <li> <span>Step 2</span> Take a pan with water and put it on the stove. Then add salt to taste, ½ tsp turmeric powder, and the previously soaked rice. Cook for about 15 minutes.\r\n   </li>\r\n   <li> <span>Step 3</span> Strain the water.</li>\r\n   <li> <span>Step 4</span> Take a pan and add 2 tbsps of coconut oil, 1 ½ tsps of split Bengal gram, 1 tsp of split skinless black gram, ½ tsp of asafoetida, 1 tsp of mustard seeds, 4 dried red chilis, ½ cup of raw peanuts and stir.\r\n   </li>\r\n   <li> <span>Step 5</span> Then add 2 sprigs of curry leaves and saute for 1 minute.\r\n   </li>\r\n   <li> <span>Step 6</span> Add the cooked rice to this mix and then sprinkle salt to taste.</li>\r\n   <li> <span>Step 7</span> Switch off the heat and add 1 tbsp lemon juice and mix it well.\r\n   </li>\r\n<li> <span>Step 8</span> Your Lemon Brown Rice is ready to serve. Top it off with coriander and you’re good to go!</li>\r\n</ul>',NULL,NULL,'daawat-brown-rice','2022-06-13 09:28:24','2024-04-26 12:44:03'),(41,'Soya Chap Tikka Biryani',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2','2','2','Veg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/18-soya-chap-tikka-biryani-1655092817.png','media/recipes/thumbnail/18-soya-chap-tikka-biryani-1655092817.jpg','2022-06-13','A true delight for all the vegetarians! Here\'s how you can relish the traditional taste of biryani with this lip-smacking \'Soya Chaap Tikka Dum Biryani\' recipe. Make sure to elevate your Biryani dish with the authentic taste and finest quality of Daawat Basmati Rice!','Easy','45-mins','2 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8Q6lpQwjRXo',1,'Soya Chaap Tikka Biryani Recipe | Daawat Soya Specialty','soya chaap tikki biryani recipe','Discover the delicious Soya Chaap Tikka Biryani recipe on Daawat. A perfect blend of flavors, this dish brings the richness of soya chaap and exotic spices together.','soya-chap',NULL,NULL,'fusion,indian','always-loved','weekend-meal,party,everyday-meal','party,dinner,lunch','<ul>\r\n<li>800 gms of soya chaap</li>\r\n<li>Mustard oil</li>\r\n<li>Kashmiri red chili powder</li>\r\n<li>Coriander powder</li>\r\n<li>Cumin powder</li>\r\n<li>Dry mango powder</li>\r\n<li>Turmeric powder</li>\r\n<li>Black salt</li>\r\n<li>Garam masala</li>\r\n<li>Kasuri methi</li>\r\n<li>Roasted gram flour</li>\r\n<li>Ginger garlic paste</li>\r\n<li>½ cup of thick curd</li>\r\n<li>Freshly chopped coriander</li>\r\n<li>Freshly chopped mint</li>\r\n<li>Lemon juice</li>\r\n<li>Salt</li>\r\n<li>Live Charcoal</li>\r\n<li>Ghee</li>\r\n<li>Onions</li>\r\n<li>Capsicum</li>\r\n<li>Tomatoes</li>\r\n<li>Melted butter</li>\r\n<li>Cumin seeds</li>\r\n<li>Bay leaf</li>\r\n<li>1 inch cinnamon stick</li>\r\n<li>Green cardamoms</li>\r\n<li>Ginger garlic paste</li>\r\n<li>Peppercorns</li>\r\n<li>Star Anise</li>\r\n<li>Cloves</li>\r\n<li>Javitri</li>\r\n<li>Saffron infused milk</li>\r\n<li>Kewra water</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n<li><span>Step 1</span> Take 800 gms of soya chaap and deep fry until crisp and golden brown.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 2</span> Cut the fried soya chaap into 2-3 pieces diagonally.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 3</span> Take a pan, and add 1 tbsp mustard oil and 1 tbsp Kashmiri red chili powder to give better color to the marinade.\r\n</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 4</span> Add 1 tbsp coriander powder, 1 tbsp cumin powder, 1 tsp dry mango powder, ½ tsp turmeric powder, ½ tsp black salt, 1 tsp garam masala, 1 tsp kasuri methi, 1 tsp roasted gram flour, and 1 tbsp ginger garlic paste. Now mix it all well.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 5</span> Add ½ a cup of thick curd, 1 tbsp of freshly chopped coriander, 1 tbsp of freshly chopped mint, 1 tsp lemon juice, and salt as per taste. Mix it all together and make sure there are no lumps.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 6</span> Add ½ a cup of onion petals, ½ a cup of diced capsicum, ½ a cup of diced and deseeded tomatoes, and finally add the fried soya chaap. Mix it all gently.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step7</span> Add live charcoal and ghee, and cover for 4-5 minutes to impart the smoky flavor into the soya chaap tikka.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 8</span> Skew the soya chaap along with capsicum, tomatoes, and onions on a skewer. Cook on an open flame.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 9</span> Apply melted butter and briefly cook again on a direct flame. Now your soya chaap tikka is ready!</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 10</span> Now take a pot and add 1 tbsp of ghee, 1 tsp cumin seeds, 1 bay leaf, 1-inch cinnamon stick, and 2 green cardamoms. Cook briefly for 30 seconds to a minute on a medium flame.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 11</span> Add 1 cup of sliced onions and cook until the onions are golden brown in color.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 12</span> Add 1 tbsp ginger garlic paste, and 2 chopped-up green chilies, and cook for 1-2 minutes on a medium flame. Now add 1 tbsp Kashmiri red chili powder, 1 tbsp coriander powder, 1 tbsp cumin powder, and ½ tsp turmeric powder, and stir and mix well. Make sure to add some hot water to avoid the masalas from burning. Cook on medium flame until the ghee is released from the masala.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 13</span> Add 2-3 medium-sized sliced tomatoes and sprinkle some salt to taste. Cook until the tomatoes are really mushy. Further, cook well until the ghee is released from the masala.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 14</span> Lower the heat and add 1 cup of whisked curd. Continuously stir and mix well for 2 minutes. Increase the heat to medium-high flame and cook well for 5-6 minutes, or until the ghee is released.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 15</span> Add a pinch of garam masala, 1 tsp of kasuri methi, a handful of fresh coriander, and a handful of fresh mint. Stir and mix well. Then add the soya chaap tikka and again stir well. Add 100-200 ml of hot water to this mix and stir, then switch off the flame.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 16</span> Add 500 gms of Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice to a pan and wash it well 3 times. Soak the rice in fresh water for 15-20 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 17</span> In a pot, boil some water, and add 1 bay leaf, 7-8 black peppercorns, 1-star anise, 3-4 cloves, 1-inch cinnamon stick, 1 javitri, 2-3 green cardamoms, 1 tsp cumin seeds, salt to taste, 1 tbsp freshly chopped coriander, 1 tbsp freshly chopped mint, and 1 tbsp ghee.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 18</span> Drain the water and add the soaked rice. Cook for 7-8 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 19</span> Then add barista fried onions, coriander leaves, mint leaves, and ghee. Cook the rice until it\'s 3/4th to almost done.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 20</span> Strain and add half of the rice on top of the soya chaap tikka masala. Sprinkle it with some barista-fried onions, coriander leaves, mint leaves, garam masala, and saffron-infused milk, and then add the second layer of rice on top.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 21</span> Again top it off with coriander leaves, mint leaves, garam masala, saffron-infused milk, ghee, and kewra water.\r\n</li><li><span>Step 22</span> Apply dough on the rim of the vessel, place a lid, and seal.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 23</span> Place a Tawa under the vessel. Cook on the dum on high heat for the initial 10 minutes. Then lower the flame and cook for another 10 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 24</span> Your soya chaap tikka biryani is ready to serve!</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>',NULL,NULL,'daawat-biryani-rice','2022-06-13 09:30:17','2024-04-26 12:42:10'),(42,'Easy Paneer Biryani',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2','2','2','Veg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/19-paneer-biryani-1655093008.png','media/recipes/thumbnail/19-paneer-biryani-1655093008.png','2022-06-13','Biryani yaani...Daawat! Today\'s special: Paneer Biryani that you can cook and enjoy at home. The secret to nailing this lip-smacking Paneer Biryani is the finest quality of long-grain rice. Kyuki jab Daawat long grain Basmati Rice se khana banega, toh farq dikhega.','Easy','45-mins','2 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wgkMVx36-SY',1,'Easy Paneer Biryani Recipe | Quick & Delicious - Daawat','easy paneer biryani recipe','Whip up a delicious meal with Daawat\'s Easy Paneer Biryani Recipe. Perfect for busy days, this recipe combines flavorful spices and paneer for a satisfying feast.','easy-paneer-biryani',NULL,NULL,NULL,'always-loved',NULL,NULL,'<ul>\r\n<li>   500 grams cottage cheese (paneer), cut into 1-inch cubes</li>\r\n<li>51½ cups Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice</li>\r\n<li>Salt to taste</li>\r\n<li>7-8 black peppercorns</li>\r\n<li>3-4 green cardamoms</li>\r\n<li>2-3 cloves</li>\r\n<li>2-3 tbsps ghee</li>\r\n<li>3-4 cloves</li>\r\n<li>6-8 black peppercorns</li>\r\n<li>2 green cardamoms</li>\r\n<li>1-2 bay leaves</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp cumin seeds</li>\r\n<li>2-3 green chilies, slit</li>\r\n<li>2 large onions, thinly sliced</li>\r\n<li>1½ tbsps ginger-garlic paste</li>\r\n<li>1 cup fresh tomato puree</li>\r\n<li>Salt to taste</li>\r\n<li>2 tsp red chili powder</li>\r\n<li>½ tsp turmeric powder</li>\r\n<li>¾ tsp coriander powder</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp cumin powder</li>\r\n<li>1½ tbsps biryani masala</li>\r\n<li>3 tbsps browned onions</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsps chopped fresh mint leaves</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp chopped fresh coriander leaves</li>\r\n<li>2-3 tsp butter</li>\r\n<li>2-3 tbsps yogurt</li>\r\n<li>A large pinch of saffron, soaked in 1-2 tbsps warm wat</li>\r\n<li>2-3 tsp rose water</li>\r\n<li>1-2 tsp screwpine (kewra) water</li>\r\n<li>Ghee for drizzling</li>\r\n<li>¼ cup browned onions + for garnish</li>\r\n<li>12-15 fresh coriander sprigs</li>\r\n<li>10-12 fresh mint leaves</li>\r\n<li>2-3 green chilies, slit</li>\r\n<li>1-inch ginger, cut into thin strips</li>\r\n<li>1-2 tsp dried rose petals</li>\r\n<li>Fresh mint sprig for garnish</li>\r\n<li>Boondi raita as required</li>\r\n<li>Onion rings</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n <li><span>Step 1</span> Take Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice in a bowl. Add sufficient water and wash 2-3 times.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 2</span> Add some fresh water and let it soak for 25-30 minutes. Now drain the water.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 3</span> Boil 6-8 cups of water in a deep non-stick pan. Add salt, black peppercorns, green cardamoms, and cloves. Now add the soaked rice, mix, and then cook for 10-15 minutes, or till the rice is ¾ done. Again, drain the rice.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 4</span> To make the masala, heat ghee in a deep pan. Add cloves, black peppercorns, green cardamoms, bay leaves, cumin seeds, green chilies, and onions, and now sauté till golden brown.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 5</span> Add ginger-garlic paste, mix, and cook for 1-2 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 6</span> Pour the tomato puree and mix well. Add salt, mix, and cook for 2-3 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 7</span> Add red chili powder, turmeric powder, coriander powder, cumin powder, biryani masala, browned onions, mint leaves, coriander leaves, and butter. Now mix well, and then cook on medium heat till the fat separates.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 8</span> Reduce the heat to low, add yogurt, and mix well. Add ½ cup water, mix, and cook for 3-4 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 9</span> Add the paneer cubes and gently mix till well combined. Evenly spread the cooked rice over the paneer masala. Drizzle soaked saffron, rose water, screwpine water, and ghee. Now sprinkle browned onions, coriander sprigs, mint leaves, green chilies, ginger, and dried rose petals.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 10</span> Cover the pan with aluminum foil and place the lid on it. Cook on low heat for 8-10 minutes. Once done, switch the heat off and transfer the paneer biryani to a serving plate.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 11</span> Garnish with browned onions and mint sprig. Serve hot with boondi raita and onion rings.</li>\r\n    \r\n</ul>',NULL,NULL,'daawat-biryani-rice','2022-06-13 09:32:50','2024-04-26 12:23:34'),(43,'Chicken Tikka Biryani',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2','2','2','NonVeg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/20-chicken-tikka-biryani-1655093094.png','media/recipes/thumbnail/20-chicken-tikka-biryani-1655093094.jpg','2022-06-13','Presenting a feast for your senses as we combine your favorite Tikka Masala flavor with the finest quality Daawat Basmati Rice. Dig into the spicy, flavourful and extremely delicious Chicken Tikka Biryani from the comfort of your home! \r\n\r\nSo, put on your chef\'s hat as this protein-packed goodness is just a few steps away from you.','Easy','45-mins','3 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Gjx4nPQwch0',1,'Chicken Tikka Biryani Recipe | Spicy & Flavorful Feast - Daawat','chicken tikka biryani recipe','Indulge in the spicy and smoky flavors of Daawat\'s Chicken Tikka Biryani Recipe. A delightful fusion of juicy chicken tikka pieces with aromatic basmati rice, this recipe promises an unforgettable culinary experience. Perfect for any celebration.','chicken-tikka-biryani',NULL,NULL,'fusion,indian','always-loved','weekend-meal,party','party','<ul>\r\n<li>4 cups of Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice</li>\r\n<li>Water</li>\r\n<li>8-10 black peppers</li>\r\n<li>2 cinnamon sticks</li>\r\n<li>4 cardamoms</li>\r\n<li>6 cloves</li>\r\n<li>1.5 tsp of salt</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp ginger</li>\r\n<li>Ghee</li>\r\n<li>1 cup of curd</li>\r\n<li>1.5 tbsp mustard oil</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp chili powder</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp garam masala</li>\r\n<li>1 tsp black pepper powder</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp chili paste</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp ginger garlic paste</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp vinegar</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp Kasuri methi</li>\r\n<li>Salt</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsps chopped coriander</li>\r\n<li>1 kg chicken breast</li>\r\n<li>½ a cup of chopped onions</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp chopped garlic</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp chopped ginger</li>\r\n<li>1 cup chopped tomatoes</li>\r\n<li>½ tsp of garam masala</li>\r\n<li>½ tsp biryani masala</li>\r\n<li>1 cup tomato puree</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp red food coloring</li>\r\n<li>Mint leaves</li>\r\n<li>Fried onions</li>\r\n<li>Kewra water</li>\r\n<li>Diced onion rings</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n <li><span>Step 1</span> Take 4 cups of Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice and wash it properly with water 2-3 times. Then soak it in fresh water for 1 hour.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 2</span> Add 6 cups of water to a pan. Then add 8-10 black peppers, 2 cinnamon sticks, 4 cardamoms,  6 cloves, 1.5 tsp of salt, 1 tsp ginger, and 1 tsp ghee.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 3</span> Now add the soaked rice to this mix, cover, and cook for 5-6 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 4</span> Take another pan and add 1 cup of curd, 1.5 tbsp mustard oil, 1 tsp chili powder, 1 tbsp garam masala, 1 tsp black pepper powder, 1 tbsp chili paste, 1 tbsp ginger garlic paste, 1 tbsp vinegar, 1 tbsp Kasuri methi, salt to taste, and 2 tbsps chopped coriander. Then whisk it all together.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 5</span> Then add 1 kg chicken breast and marinate the mixture for 30 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 6</span> Add 1 tbsp of oil to a pan and then add the chicken to it. Cook on low heat for 10 minutes. Flip halfway.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 7</span> In another different pan add 1 tbsp of ghee, ½ a cup of chopped onions, 1 tbsp chopped garlic, 1 tbsp chopped ginger, 1 cup of chopped tomatoes, and salt to taste. Add ½ tsp of garam masala, ½ tsp Biryani masala, 1 cup of tomato puree, and the previously prepared marinated paste.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 8</span> Add 1 tbsp red food coloring to the mix, 1 cup water, and the prepared chicken. Then add the prepared rice, mint leaves, fried onions, and kewra water.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 9</span> Add another layer of the prepared chicken and then a layer of the prepared rice on top. Top it off with some mint leaves, fried onions, and kewra water.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 10</span> Seal the vessel with kneaded dough, cover, and cook for 10 minutes. Finally garnish with mint leaves and diced onion rings, and your Chicken Tikka Biryani is ready to serve!</li>\r\n</ul>',NULL,NULL,'daawat-biryani-rice','2022-06-13 09:34:54','2024-04-26 12:04:42'),(44,'Vegetable Biryani',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2','2','2','Veg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/21-veg-biryani-1655093200.png','media/recipes/thumbnail/21-veg-biryani-1655093200.png','2022-06-13','Transforming your Daawat Basmati rice into a lip-smacking Biryani is extremely simple and this recipe will show you how!','Easy','45-mins','3 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=14H53zt7ERU&t=13s',1,'Vegetable Biryani Recipe | Perfect Homemade - Daawat','vegetable biryani recipe','Discover the ultimate Vegetable Biryani Recipe at Daawat.com. Our authentic homemade guide ensures a flavorful and aromatic biryani every time. Perfect for any occasion.','vegetable-biryani',NULL,NULL,'fusion,indian','always-loved','weekend-meal','party','<ul>\r\n   <li>&nbsp;2 Medium Carrots, Peeled And Cut Into Diamond</li>\r\n<li> 10-12 Cauliflower Florets</li>\r\n<li> 5-6 French Beans, Cut Into Pieces</li>\r\n<li> 4-5 Baby Corn, Cut Into Diamonds</li>\r\n<li> ¼ Cup Green Peas</li>\r\n<li> 100 Grams of Cottage Cheese (Paneer), Cut Into Small Cubes</li>\r\n<li> 1½ Cups Daawat Super Basmati Rice, Soaked For 30 Minutes And Drained</li>\r\n<li> 4 Tablespoons Ghee + For Drizzling And Brushing</li>\r\n<li> 1 Inch Cinnamon</li>\r\n<li> 5 Green Cardamoms</li>\r\n<li> 1 Blade Mace (Javitri)</li>\r\n<li> 10-12 Cloves</li>\r\n<li> 10-12 Black Peppercorns</li>\r\n<li> 1 Bay Leaf</li>\r\n<li> 1 Teaspoon Caraway Seeds (Shahi Jeera)</li>\r\n<li> 1 Large Onion, Sliced</li>\r\n<li> 2 Green Chillies</li>\r\n<li> 1½ Tablespoons Ginger-Garlic Paste</li>\r\n<li> ¼ Teaspoon Turmeric Powder</li>\r\n<li> 1 Teaspoon Coriander-Cumin Powder</li>\r\n<li> 1 Teaspoon Red Chilli Powder</li>\r\n<li> ½ Cup Fresh Tomato Puree</li>\r\n<li> 2 Tablespoons Fresh Cream</li>\r\n<li> 1 Tablespoon Chopped Fresh Coriander Leaves</li>\r\n<li> 4 Tablespoons Fried Onions</li>\r\n<li> Green Cardamom Powder For Sprinkling</li>\r\n<li> 1 Inch Ginger, Cut Into Strips</li>\r\n<li> 8-10 Raisins</li>\r\n<li> 8-10 Cashew Nuts, Roasted</li>\r\n<li> Screwpine Essence (Kewra) For Drizzling</li>\r\n<li> 4 Teaspoons Saffron Milk + For Brushing</li>\r\n<li> Few Fresh Mint Leaves</li>\r\n<li> Refined Flour (Maida) Or Whole Wheat Flour (Atta) Roti For Covering</li>\r\n   \r\n</ul>',NULL,NULL,NULL,'daawat-biryani-rice','2022-06-13 09:36:40','2024-04-26 12:32:16'),(45,'Hyderabadi Mutton Biryani',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2','2','2','NonVeg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/22-hyderabadi-mutton-biryani-1655093293.png','media/recipes/thumbnail/22-hyderabadi-mutton-biryani-1655093293.png','2022-06-13','Feast of the delicious Hyderabadi Mutton Biryani with the Worlds Longest Basmati Grain.','Easy','45-mins','4 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=clHwZ61t-_g&t=7s',1,'Hyderabadi Mutton Biryani Recipe | Rich & Flavorful - Daawat','hyderabadi mutton biryani recipe','Master the art of Hyderabadi cuisine with Daawat\'s Hyderabadi Mutton Biryani Recipe. Dive into the rich flavors and tender mutton pieces layered with aromatic basmati rice, cooked to perfection. This recipe brings the authentic taste of Hyderabad to your table. Cook and relish every bite.','hyderabadi-mutton-biryani',NULL,NULL,'fusion,indian','always-loved','weekend-meal,party','party,dinner,lunch','<ul>\r\n<li>1 ½ cups of Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice</li>\r\n<li>6-18 black peppercorns</li>\r\n<li>1 black cardamom</li>\r\n<li>7 green cardamoms</li>\r\n<li>1 star anise</li>\r\n<li>1-inch cinnamon</li>\r\n<li>2 bay leaves</li>\r\n<li>8-10 cloves</li>\r\n<li>Salt</li>\r\n<li>1 cup yogurt</li>\r\n<li>3 tbsps ginger garlic paste</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp red chili powder</li>\r\n<li>Garam masala powder</li>\r\n<li>750 gms of mutton, cut into 1-inch pieces on the bone</li>\r\n<li>10-12 dried plums</li>\r\n<li>Fresh mint leaves</li>\r\n<li>8-10 fresh coriander sprigs</li>\r\n<li>Fried onions</li>\r\n<li>Ghee</li>\r\n<li>Uncut green chilies</li>\r\n<li>Screw pine essence (kewra)</li>\r\n<li>Saffron milk</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n   <li><span>Step 1</span> Boil water in a pot. Add 16-18 black peppercorns, 1 black cardamom, 7 green cardamoms, 1 star anise, 1-inch cinnamon, 2 bay leaves, 8-10 cloves, salt to taste, and 1 ½ cups of Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice, Now let it cook.</li>\r\n \r\n<li><span>Step 2</span> Take another pot and add 1 cup yogurt, 3 tbsp ginger garlic paste, 1 tbsp red chili powder, 2 tsp garam masala powder, and salt to taste.</li>\r\n\r\n<li><span>Step 3</span> Now add 750 gms of mutton, cut into 1-inch pieces on the bone. Add 10-12 dried plums to this mixture and mix it all together. Add 16-18 fresh mint leaves, 8-10 fresh coriander sprigs, ½ cup fried onions, and 2 tbsp ghee, and let it cook.</li>\r\n\r\n<li><span>Step 4</span> Now take a pot that is oven friendly and add the mutton to it. Add 4 uncut green chilies and set it aside.</li>\r\n\r\n<li><span>Step 5</span> Now remove the black cardamom and the bay leaf from it and strain the rice.</li>\r\n\r\n<li><span>Step 6</span> Spread a layer of the Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice on top of the mutton, add 1 tbsp of ghee, 2 tsp of garam masala powder, ½ cup of fried onions, 12-15 fresh mint leaves, a few drops of screw pine essence (kewra), and 2 tbsps saffron milk. Top it off with a layer of mutton.</li>\r\n\r\n<li><span>Step 7</span> Add 3 uncut green chilies to it and add a second layer of Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice on top.</li>\r\n\r\n<li><span>Step 8</span> Add ¼ cup of fried onions, 10-12 fresh mint leaves, a pinch of garam masala powder, 2 tbsps of saffron milk, 2 tbsps of ghee, and some screw pine essence (kewra).</li>\r\n\r\n<li><span>Step 9</span> Now put some dough on the lid of the vessel, seal it, and put it on the flame.</li>\r\n\r\n<li><span>Step 10</span> Your Hyderabadi Mutton Biryani is ready! Remove the lid only when you’re ready to serve!</li>\r\n</ul>',NULL,NULL,'daawat-biryani-rice','2022-06-13 09:38:13','2024-04-26 11:59:21'),(46,'Kashmiri Mutton Biryani',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2','2','2','NonVeg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/23-kashmiri-mutton-biryani-1655093372.png','media/recipes/thumbnail/23-kashmiri-mutton-biryani-1655093372.png','2022-06-13',NULL,'Easy','40-45-minutes','3 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Az8tEw3YaPM&t=6s',1,'Kashmiri Mutton Biryani Recipe | Rich & Aromatic Delight - Daawat','kashmiri mutton biryani recipe','Experience the heavenly blend of delicate spices and tender mutton in Daawat\'s Kashmiri Mutton Biryani Recipe. Infused with the traditional flavors of Kashmir, this biryani recipe is a luxurious treat for your taste buds.','kashmiri-mutton-biryani',NULL,NULL,'kashmiri','always-loved','weekend-meal,party','party,dinner,lunch','<ul>\r\n<li>500 grams mutton, cut into 1-inch pieces on the bone</li>\r\n<li>1½ cups Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice</li>\r\n<li>5 tablespoons ghee</li>\r\n<li>1 tablespoon fennel seeds (saunf)</li>\r\n<li>3 bay leaves</li>\r\n<li>10-12 cloves</li>\r\n<li>7 green cardamoms</li>\r\n<li>1-inch cinnamon</li>\r\n<li>5 green chilies</li>\r\n<li>Salt to taste</li>\r\n<li>1 tablespoon ginger-garlic paste</li>\r\n<li>2 teaspoons caraway seeds (shahi jeera)</li>\r\n<li>1 tablespoon fennel (saunf) powder</li>\r\n<li>½ teaspoon dried ginger powder (saunth)</li>\r\n<li>¼ teaspoon mace (javitri) powder</li>\r\n<li>¼ cup yogurt</li>\r\n<li>2 tablespoons saffron milk</li>\r\n<li>few drops of rose water</li>\r\n<li>fresh mint sprig for garnishing</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n   <li><span>Step 1</span> Soak the Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice in sufficient water for 30 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 2</span> Heat 2 tablespoons of ghee in a pressure cooker.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 3</span> Take a piece of muslin cloth. add fennel seeds, and tie them into a potli.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 4</span> Add the bay leaves, cloves, green cardamoms, cinnamon, and broken green chilies to the ghee, and sauté for a minute.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 5</span> Add the mutton pieces and mix. Now add salt, mix, and sauté till the mutton pieces are lightly browned.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 6</span> Add ginger-garlic paste and mix well. Then add sufficient water to it, and stir to mix. Add the potli, cover, and pressure cook for 15-20 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 7</span> Discard the potli and strain the mutton pieces. Discard the bay leaves and cinnamon as well, and reserve the mutton stock.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 8</span> Heat the remaining ghee in a deep non-stick pan. Add the caraway seeds and sauté till the seeds crackle.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 9</span> Add the mutton pieces, the fennel powder, ginger powder, and mace powder, and mix well. Now add yogurt, mix, and bring to a boil.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 10</span> Add 3 cups of reserved mutton stock and the drained Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice. Cover it, and then bring it to a boil.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 11</span> Add the saffron milk and rose water and cover again. Now cook on low heat for 10-12 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 12</span> Finally, garnish with mint sprig and serve hot.</li>\r\n</ul>',NULL,NULL,'daawat-biryani-rice','2022-06-13 09:39:32','2024-04-26 12:05:42'),(47,'Anda Biryani',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2','2','2','NonVeg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/24-egg-biryani-1655093491.png','media/recipes/thumbnail/24-egg-biryani-1655093491.png','2022-06-13','Are you an egg lover? Then this is for you! A wholesome one-pot meal prepared with aromatic Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice, hard-boiled eggs, and topped with veggies!','Easy','45-mins','3 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dFfyhP63E90&t=16s',1,'Anda Biryani Recipe | Easy & Flavorful - Daawat','anda biryani recipe','Indulge in the rich flavors of Anda Biryani with Daawat\'s authentic recipe. Perfect blend of spices and eggs, this Anda Biryani Recipe is a must-try for all.','anda-biryani',NULL,NULL,'indian','winter-special','weekend-meal,party,everyday-meal','dinner,lunch','<ul>\r\n<li>8 eggs (anda), hard-boiled and peeled</li>\r\n<li>1½ cups Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice, soaked for 30 minutes and drained</li>\r\n<li>4 tbsps oil</li>\r\n<li>1 black cardamom</li>\r\n<li>½ inch cinnamon</li>\r\n<li>1 bay leaf</li>\r\n<li>18 cloves</li>\r\n<li>12-16 black peppercorns</li>\r\n<li>9 green cardamoms</li>\r\n<li>1 large onion, finely chopped</li>\r\n<li>4 medium potatoes, boiled and peeled</li>\r\n<li>Salt to taste</li>\r\n<li>Juice of ½ lemon</li>\r\n<li>½ tsp turmeric powder</li>\r\n<li>2 tsps red chili powder</li>\r\n<li>1½ tbsps ginger-garlic paste</li>\r\n<li>3 green chilies</li>\r\n<li>¾ cup fresh tomato puree</li>\r\n<li>2 tbsps coriander powder</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp + a pinch of garam masala powder</li>\r\n<li>1 tbsp chopped fresh coriander leaves</li>\r\n<li>¼&nbsp; cup yogurt</li>\r\n<li>3 tbsps of fried onions + a few fresh mint leaves for garnishing</li>\r\n<li>1-inch ginger, cut into strips</li>\r\n<li>Fresh mint sprig for garnishing</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n <li><span>Step 1</span> Heat 2 tbsps of oil in a deep non-stick pan.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 2</span> Heat 3 cups of water in another deep non-stick pan. Add 1 black cardamom, ½ inch cinnamon, 1 bay leaf, 8 of the cloves, black peppercorns, and 4 green cardamoms to the water. Bring the whole thing to a boil.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 3</span> Add remaining cloves and remaining green cardamoms to the oil and sauté till fragrant.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 4</span> Add the Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice to the boiling water and let it cook.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 5</span> Add onions to the oil and sauté until translucent.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 6</span> Cut the potatoes into cubes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 7</span> Add salt, 1 tbsp oil, and lemon juice to the Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice and cook till ¾th done.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 8</span> Add ¼ tsp turmeric powder and 1½ tsps chili powder to the onions and mix well. Now add eggs and potato cubes to it, and fry for a minute. Transfer the eggs and potatoes to a bowl and set aside.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 9</span> Add the ginger-garlic paste and mix. Then add green chilies, tomato puree, and salt. Mix it all well and cook for 2-3 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 10</span> Strain the Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice in a colander and set it aside.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 11</span> Add coriander powder, remaining chili powder, 1 tbsp garam masala powder, and the remaining turmeric powder to the tomato puree mixture. Mix it well and cook till the oil separates.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 12</span> Add the fried eggs (anda), potato cubes, coriander leaves, and yogurt, and spread a layer of strained Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice on top.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 13</span> Top it with fried onions, some mint leaves, a pinch of garam masala powder, and ginger strips. Add the remaining oil, then cover and cook on medium heat for 20 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 14 Finally, garnish with fried onions and mint sprig, and serve hot.</span></li>\r\n  \r\n</ul>',NULL,NULL,'daawat-biryani-rice','2022-06-13 09:41:31','2024-04-26 12:26:50'),(48,'Hyderabadi Dum Chicken Biryani',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2','2','2','NonVeg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/25-hyderabadi-chicken-dum-biryani-1655093632.png','media/recipes/thumbnail/25-hyderabadi-chicken-dum-biryani-1655093632.png','2022-06-13','Enhancing the taste of Hyderabadi Chicken Biryani with the world\'s longest Basmati grain; Daawat Biryani Basmati.','Easy','45-mins','4 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0kxuFVG-Gh4&t=2s',1,'Hyderabadi Dum Chicken Biryani Recipe | Authentic & Delicious - Daawat','hyderabadi dum chicken biryani recipe','Bring the true essence of Hyderabadi cuisine into your kitchen with Daawat\'s Hyderabadi Dum Chicken Biryani Recipe. This authentic recipe layers succulent chicken with flavorful basmati rice, slow-cooked to perfection.','hyderabadi-dum-chicken-biryani',NULL,NULL,'fusion,indian','always-loved','party','party','<ul>\r\n<li>1½&nbsp; cups of Daawat Biryani Basmati rice, soaked</li>\r\n<li>6 green cardamoms</li>\r\n<li>2 black cardamoms</li>\r\n<li>1 blade mace (Javitri)</li>\r\n<li>1-inch cinnamon</li>\r\n<li>6-8 cloves</li>\r\n<li>8-10 black peppercorns</li>\r\n<li>1 star anise (Phool chakri)</li>\r\n<li>1 teaspoon of ginger-garlic paste</li>\r\n<li>2-3 green chilies, finely chopped</li>\r\n<li>1 cup yogurt</li>\r\n<li>¾&nbsp; cup + 6 tablespoons of fried onion, for garnishing</li>\r\n<li>12-16 fresh mint leaves</li>\r\n<li>1 teaspoon of red chili powder</li>\r\n<li>1 teaspoon of garam masala powder</li>\r\n<li>1 teaspoon of turmeric powder</li>\r\n<li>3 tablespoons of dried rose petals</li>\r\n<li>3 tablespoons of ghee</li>\r\n<li>Whole wheat flour, dough as required</li>\r\n<li>2 green chilies</li>\r\n<li>1 inch ginger</li>\r\n<li>2 tablespoons of saffron milk</li>\r\n</ul>','<ul>\r\n   <li><span>Step 1</span> Soak Daawat Biryani Rice in sufficient water for 30 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 2</span> Take a piece of muslin cloth. Add 6 green cardamoms, 2 black cardamoms, mace, cinnamon, 6-8 cloves, 8-10 peppercorns, star anise, and 1 ⁄ 2 teaspoon of caraway seeds. Now tie the cloth into a potli.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 3</span> Heat 3 cups of water in a deep non-stick pan. Add the potli and salt as required. Now cover the pan with a lid and bring to a boil.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 4</span> Put the chicken pieces in a bowl. Add ginger-garlic paste, chopped green chilies, the remaining caraway seeds, yogurt, ¾ fried onions, 12-16 mint leaves, chili powder, turmeric powder, 1 teaspoon of garam masala powder, and 1 tablespoon of dried rose petals. Mix all of them well and set them aside to marinate.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 5</span> After draining the water it was soaking in, add the Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice to boiling water. Cover and cook until 3/4th done.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 6</span> Add salt to the chicken pieces and mix them well.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 7</span> Heat 3 tablespoons of ghee in another deep non-stick pan. Add chicken pieces with the marinade.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 8</span> Roll the wheat flour dough into a cylindrical shape and place it on the lid.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 9</span> Chop green chilies and add them to the chicken. Now mix it well and cook on high heat for 3-4 minutes.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 10</span> Discard the potli, and strain the Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice in a colander. Now add 2 tablespoons of ghee to the Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice and mix well.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 11</span> Transfer some of the chicken pieces into a bowl and set them aside.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 12</span> Spread a layer of strained Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice on the chicken pieces that were in the pan. Top it with 3 tablespoons of fried onions, 1 tablespoon of dried rose petals, and half chopped ginger. Now sprinkle some garam masala powder, add some mint leaves, and finally 1 tablespoon of saffron milk.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 13</span> Add the chicken pieces previously set aside on top, and once again spread a layer of strained Daawat Biryani Basmati Rice on top. Top it up with 3 tablespoons of fried onion, 1 tablespoon of dried rose petals, the remaining ginger strips, some mint leaves, 1 tablespoon of ghee, the remaining saffron milk, and again some garam masala powder.</li>\r\n<li><span>Step 14</span> Now place the lid with dough on top and press. Cook on low heat for 20 minutes and then serve hot.</li>\r\n</ul>',NULL,NULL,'daawat-biryani-rice','2022-06-13 09:43:52','2024-04-26 12:03:38'),(49,'Veg Pulav',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2','2','2','Veg',NULL,'media/recipes/image/32-vegetable-pulav-1655094331.png','media/recipes/thumbnail/32-vegetable-pulav-1655094331.png','2022-06-13','Transforming your Daawat Pulav Basmati rice into a lip-smacking Vegetable Pulav is extremely simple and this recipe will show you how!','Easy','30-min','2 People',NULL,NULL,'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WZaLeYcdn7Y',1,'Veg Pulav Recipe | Simple & Delicious - Daawat','veg pulav recipe','Discover the ultimate Veg Pulav Recipe on Daawat. This simple, yet delicious mix of rice and vegetables is the perfect dish for any occasion. Explore now.','veg-pulav',NULL,NULL,'fusion,indian','all-time','weekend-meal,everyday-meal','dinner,lunch',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'daawat-pulav-rice','2022-06-13 09:55:31','2024-04-26 12:28:06'),(50,'Fried 